deck_excerpt: Combo-heavy Shaddoll build feat. Predaplant Engine
deck_description:
I've been working on this particular Shaddoll build for a bit now and I'm pretty excited with the results so far. Squamatta & Wendi are your primary engine cards so you have to run 3 each. Ariel is your combo enabler with some incidental GY hate stapled to it. Keios is really just a Light tutor target to enable your plays with Construct. The rest are utility effects that you can access at almost any time you want. Performage engine enables your combos via Trick Clown. Damage Juggler can have some nice synergy with the Predeplant engine as well as granting you more utility. Hat Tricker is just a tutor target and extender, he also grants access to the Earth type in the main deck. The Predeplant engine is nice here because Shaddoll doesn't need a normal summon in-archetype but can have issues finding its Fusion spells at times. Scorpion for Cobra fixes this issue quite nicely while offering Dark type monsters to fuse with and putting bodies on the table for link summons. The fact that Scorpion can tutor any of your fusion effects is also quite nice as it offers a lot of utility. The hand trap line-up is pretty standard. Ash is the best HT in the format. Gamma protects your Shaddoll Fusion from Ash while also providing Light monsters for Construct. Veiler isn't the best HT option in the format, but we really want access to Light monsters as often as possible and Veiler is likely the next best card for the slot. Rainbow Neos is probably the portion of the deck that looks the strangest, but hear me out. There are a couple of reasons to play it over Dragoon in this deck. For one, we like the Light type monsters a lot more than the Darks, so opening with the fusion material hurts a lot less. But there is also the fact that Neos Fusion is a much better target for your Predeplant engine since you can summon the same turn you activate it. There is also a metagame aspect to this pick. Currently the deck does fine vs Drytron and Virtual World, as we play good ways to interact with them in the main deck. However, Eldlich can be an issue for the deck. Rainbow Neos is actually an incredibly strong card in this match up. All 3 effects can be absolutely backbreaking against Lich when used at the right time, and he can't be outed by a single Conquistador thanks to the GY effect of Neos Fusion. Also, and arguably most importantly, Rainbow Neos is just way cooler than Dragoon. Not a lot to talk about as far as spells go, but I will say that your 3 limited spells all offer an absolute bevy of utility for you and I would not leave home without any of them. As for traps, Incarnation is a combo enabler and utility piece in one. 2 feels like the right number. Only 1 Schism might look wrong for how powerful the card is, but it's extremely easy to access from the deck whenever you want it. Extra deck: -Shekhinaga is important as a Super Poly target vs Zoo -Construct is your best card, never leave without 3 -Apkallone offers incredible utility between both of its effects -Winda is stupid good. 1 is usually enough, but I like running 2 in case I burn one early on an Instant Fusion play or just on an early combo start. -Venom & Mudragon are easy little Super Poly targets. Venom is extra important since you can make it off of Verte Anaconda and any opponents monster you can target with Anaconda's effect. Mudragon is nice because it can also be summoned off of Instant Fusion and become any type you might be missing in a pinch. -Accesscode Talker is your combo end boss. When made with Unicorn, Talker+ Construct offers an easy 8100 damage while clearing the opponents board on the way. -Unicorn is great utility and the link-3 enabler to make big Accesscode. -Cross-Sheep is your link-climbing expert and another important piece of your main combo. -Anaconda is Anaconda. -Gravity Controller enables any opening that can make Construct or Apkallone to tutor Schism to your hand. 1-card Shaddoll Fusion combo:
  1. Activate Fusion, sending Trick Clown and Squamatta to make Construct
  2. Trigger Clown, Squamatta, and Construct. SS Clown, send Wendi and Incarnation to the GY.
  3. Trigger Wendi, set Ariel from deck.
  4. Link Construct and Clown to make Cross-Sheep, picking back up Fusion with Construct's effect.
  5. Remove Construct for Incarnation's cost to flip Ariel face-up.
  6. Trigger Ariel, summon Construct from banish into a Cross-Sheep zone.
  7. Trigger Cross-Sheep and Construct, sending El Shaddoll Fusion and summoning back Clown.
  8. Link Sheep and Construct to make Unicorn. Pitch Shaddoll Fusion to Unicorn, and pick up El Shaddoll Fusion with Construct.
  9. Link Unicorn and Ariel to make Accesscode.
  10. Fuse Clown and any Shaddoll in hand to make Construct.

deck_excerpt: 60 card Eldlich pile deck featuring: Red-Eyes, Dogmatika, Shaddoll, and Invoked engines.
deck_description: This deck uses 5 independent engines that synergize to play a control strategy focused on gaining card advantage while disrupting your opponent's plays. The deck runs 60 cards to help reduce brick hands.  The Eldlich engine is the backbone of this deck. Golden Lord can be used as a beat-stick or for back-row removal, and he enables the secondary effects of the Eldlich trap monsters. Cursed Eldland allows you to search you other Eldlich cards. Sanguine summons Golden Lord from your deck or GY and it floats into your trap monsters. The trap monsters can each float into Sanguine. Gustav Max can be made if you get both Golden Lords to help close out games.  The Red-Eyes engine is designed to turbo Dragoon. The vanillas and Fusion card are needed for the summon, and Insight and Wyvern help you get to Fusion. Link Spider allows you to make Anaconda using trap monsters, and Anaconda gives you another way to access Fusion. Dragoon is way too powerful, so you have to play him while you can. Wyvern can bring him back after he is destroyed if the conditions are met.  The Dogmatika engine gives you access to a lot of removal and extra deck hate. Ecclesia allows you to search the other parts of this engine on summon, and can be special summoned if your opponent controls an extra deck monster. Fleurdelis is a beat-stick and negate. Maximus removes cards from your opponent's extra deck and can trigger N'tss. Nadir Servant can trigger N'tss and search Ecclesia. Punishment is removal that can also trigger N'tss for an extra removal.  Ash Dragon can be sent instead of N'tss if you want a search instead of removal.  The Shaddoll engine gives you access to control and removal tools through its extra deck monsters. Construct can run over extra deck monsters. Apkallone has battle protection and negation. Winda is a special summon floodgate. The main deck monsters provide a diverse tool-box through their flip and sent to the GY effects.  The Invoked engine has the rest of your extra deck monsters. Mechaba has negates. Augoeides can destroy a monster. Purgatrio is a beat-stick with piercing. Caliga is a battle and effect floodgate. Their main deck cards search each other, and provide recursion allowing you to recycle Invocation and Aleister.  Terraforming provides an extra copy of Meltdown which is the start of your Invoked search chain. Prison is powerful removal that can be used against most decks. Torrential is a great tool for punishing over extension, and, if Golden Lord was summoned by his own effect, he is immune to the destruction.  The side deck has back-row hate and hand-traps that can be sided in as needed.

This is a Crystal Beast deck updated to be used in 2021. I'm not saying it's good, it is Crystal Beasts after all, but I think it can be competitive with some newer non-meta decks. There are a number of strategies. You can try to get Hamon out and then Rainbow Dragon or Rainbow Overdragon. The Links and XYZ monsters allow you to use your crystal beasts for something useful and then to send them to the graveyard where you can access them with support spells. You have access to Zeus through Utopia, and Rainbow Neos is great spot removal. Let's go through the cards one by one and explain what they're run for. Monsters:
  • 1x Elemental Hero Neos - Bricky, but needed for Rainbow Neos
  • 1x Rainbow Dragon - an okay boss monster, but very hard to get out, mostly used for Rainbow Neos
  • 3x Sapphire Pegasus - this card is your bread and butter. Use it to search itself and fill your back row with Crystal Beasts.
  • 2x Ruby Carbuncle - I probably think this card  is better than it is, but its effect of being able to special summon the beasts in your back row can be really useful for flooding your board with monsters you can use to link off or XYZ.
  • 1x Emerald Tortoise, 1x Amber Mammoth, 1x Topaz Tiger, 1x Amethyst Cat, 1x Cobalt Eagle - None of these cards are especially useful, mostly used for Ultimate Crystal Magic and for filling your back row.
  • 3x Ash Blossom - I mean come on. You can use this to negate so much. Very useful for shutting down your opponent and keeping yourself alive.
Spells and Traps:
  • 3x Crystal Bond - This card is so good. You can use it to search out a Sapphire Pegasus and put a Ruby Carbuncle in your back row. A lot of plays begin with this card.
  • 3x Rainbow Bridge - This card lets you search out bond, beacon, or any other spell that you might need at a given time. Very useful card.
  • 2x Rainbow Ruins - Could maybe be bumped down to one or even zero. Just useful for staying alive longer and giving you an out when you inevitably fill your entire back row with beasts.
  • 2x Crystal Abundance - This card is really good but the condition is pretty prohibitive. You can use it to flood your board and OTK or just link off the monsters. Could honestly be bumped to three, but only if you think it's actually good.
  • 3x Crystal Promise - Great with sapphire pegasus as a way to get out Rainbow Neos instantly. Normal summon a pegasus, search out a pegasus, use promise to special summon the second pegasus, then you can link them off into verte anaconda and summon Rainbow Neos.
  • 3x Crystal Beacon - Good for an OTK that the deck is kind of built around. More on that later.
  • 1x Crystal Blessing - I think this is the worst crystal spell I included. It's good to fill your backrow after linking, but useless otherwise and bricky if you don't have any beasts in your graveyard.
  • 1x Neos Fusion - You only really need one for verte anaconda, but you could maybe run two if you also bumped up your Rainbow Neos materials.
  • 1x Raigeki - Pretty self explanatory, destroy your opponent's monsters.
  • 1x Harpie's Feather Duster - Pretty self explanatory, destroy your opponent's back row.
  • 2x Ultimate Crystal Magic - Lets you get out Rainbow Overdragon. Pretty good, easy to activate, could probably be bumped to three.
  • 1x Crystal Conclave - I do not think this card is as good as other people make it out to be. Special summoning is nice, but it takes up a zone in your back row that could otherwise be a beast.
  • 1x Infinite Impermanence - Deal with your opponents effect monsters and negate them.
  • 1x Witch's Strike - Great for getting back at your opponent when they negate a summon.
Side Deck: I think this deck actually has a lot of potential for the side deck. I listed a lot of cards that could be bumped down. You could definitely drop the  5 crystal beasts, a Neos Fusion, and so on and then fill up on hand traps or whatever else you need.
  • 2x Nibiru - This card is great against certain decks. This card is a one card OTK enabler.
  • 2x Hamon - This card can act as a replacement boss monster if you want another win condition, but getting out Rainbow Neos is probably easier.
  • 1x Topaz Tiger, 1x Emerald Tortoise, 1x Cobalt Eagle, 1x Amethyst Cat, 1x Amber Mammoth - Hey these cards aren't very good. You could probably drop them from the side deck for more tech cards. I just included them in case you want to add them for your second Ultimate Crystal Magic.
  • 1x Neos Fusion - Could probably be dropped for more tech cards, just include if you want a back up for the first one getting Ashed.
  • 2x Infinite Impermanence - Great card, great negation, really good if you go second.
  • 1x Twin Twisters - More back row removal
  • 1x Solemn Warning - You wanted to summon that monster? Damn bro, that sucks.
  • 1x Dark Ruler No More - this lets you deal with pesky effects and annoying monsters like Dragoon.
Extra Deck:
  • 1x Rainbow Overdragon - Good boss monster, not as good as Rainbow Neos
  • 1x Rainbow Neos - Really good card. Great removal that doesn't destroy or target. Very easy to get out with Verte Anaconda. This card is so good and could probably be bumped up to two.
  • 1x Daigusto Emeral, 1x Tornado Dragon, 1x Abyss Dweller - Generic rank 4 XYZ monsters that let you have various utility like back row removal or drawing cards.
  • 1x Gossip Shadow - Rank 3 for the few times you want to and can go into those. Great monster negate that lets you draw.
  • 1x Utopia, 1x Utopia the Lightning, 1x Zeus - You can evolve Utopia into Lightning, attack, then summon out Zeus with 4 materials. Zeus is great, you can shuffle out whatever your opponent puts out.
  • 1x Knightmare Cerberus, 1x Knightmare Phoenix, 1x Knightmare Unicorn - You basically have to run these cards in any deck. They're easy spot removal that you can get out for basically nothing.
  • I:P Masquerena - Good interruption. Great card, easy to get out.
  • Verte Anaconda - Kinda the backbone of this deck. Get it out as fast as possible and get out Rainbow Neos.
Example 2 Card Combo  Imagine you draw Crystal Bond and Crystal Beacon. This has the possibility to be an OTK. Either of these cards could also be a Rainbow Bridge. Anyway, start with Crystal Bond and search out a pegasus and put whatever in your back row. Normal summon Pegasus, put another pegasus in your back row. Use beacon to special summon Carbuncle from your deck. Use carbuncle's effect to summon up the pegasus and the other crystal beast. You now have two pegasus, a carbuncle, and another crystal beast. on your field. Link off the carbuncle and other crystal beast into Verte Anaconda, use it to summon Rainbow Neos, then tribute your Verte Anaconda to wipe your opponent's monsters. Now you have 8100 Attack points, just barely enough to OTK. This combo gets even better if you can add a promise into the mix.
Basic True Draco strategy that we have all seen by now not anything new to see here... Hoping to see True King's Return to 3, Dinomight to 3 and Master Peace to 1 in the next banlist.

deck_excerpt: Pure Red-Eyes deck, main card is Dark Dragoon. Claw of Hermos side deck for fun/casual play. Sort of meta since the main card is Dragoon.
deck_description: This is a pure red-eyes deck with a hermos side deck for fun. If you are playing casually I recommend siding in Hermos (or side him in whenever you want). if you don't draw Red-Eyes fusion there is still a way to get Red-Eyes Dark Dragoon on the field; Predaplant verte anaconda. Just pay 2000LP, send Red-Eyes fusion, DM and REBD to the grave. It's not easy to get Anaconda on the field as you need 2 monsters to link summon it, but its still a decent back-up plan if you don't draw Red-Eyes Fusion. Main Deck and Side Deck (40 cards) (15 cards) I put more monsters than spells/traps mainly because the Red-Eyes archetype has many monsters but not too many good spells/traps. This deck is also gemini, so say hello to Phoenix Gearfried! Gemini ablation is for getting Red-Eyes Black Flare Dragon and Phoenix Gearfried on the field (as well as the other gemini's). Gemini summoner is for when you can't fusion summon but you have a powerful gemini card in your hand. 8x Fusion cards: Claw of Hermos x3 (In the side deck), 3x Red-Eyes Fusion and 2x Polymerization for fusion summoning the fusion dragon cards. I added 3x Ash Blossom (side deck) and 2x Ghost Ogre because I couldn't find enough spells/traps, so instead I chose handtraps. Luckily Ghost Ogre is quite reliable. Extra deck (9 cards but 4 cards in the side-deck) The extra deck contains powerful cards which are part of the Red-Eyes archetype. Clearwing is just for taking full advantage of the handtraps (the handtraps are tuners).

deck_excerpt: Third update to my Endymion deck. I honestly just change it every time I hit a losing streak and then post it on here if it successfully breaks my los
deck_description: This is my third Endymion deck. I honestly just like posting it on here every time I update my deck.  I started using Chronograph Sorcerer and Timegazer Magician. I can not believe I did not use them before. Chronograph is a free spell for counters, and makes Timegazer a free special summon (I think this might have been common knowledge but keep in mind I started playing Yugioh like late-December of 2020). Not only that, but if you have a second Chronograph in hand, and you pop Chronograph to bring out Timegazer, then that activates Chronograph's effect to special summon itself from your hand, as well as any other monster from your hand that you want to special summon. That's an instant Crowley for the spellbook engine and you haven't even normal summoned yet (also if you want to keep 'em there, Timegazer has low atk/def values but acts as additional protection for your scales). If you can activate instant fusion to get out Millennium-Eyes Restrict, or activate Servant of Endymion to bring out Jackal King before you link into Crowley then you are basically free to run to grab more counters and also thin out your deck a bit more.  There is also one copy of Super Polymerization. From what I understand, most people say to run 3 or none at all, but honestly with this you are drawing into your deck so much that you either get your ideal board of negates or you draw into Super Poly anyways. This is here because I am tired of going against a first turn Dragoon with a mediocre hand. This way, I usually either have a solid hand that can play around Dragoon's negate and then finish my combo to get accesscode or something and just walk over Dragoon anyways, OR I'll have Super Poly and just take him out for Starving Venom.  Speaking of the extra deck, I took out Day-breaker and Bagooska for Starving Venom and Mudragon. I usually will always try to go for Starving Venom, especially against monsters like Dragoon and Borrelend, but if can't, Mudragon is a good way to interrupt plays as well, especially because if I activate its effect to prevent the targeting of a specific attribute, I can actually stop a surprising amount of combos (though usually if they are able to, they will just go into battle phase and walk over your Mudragon-- it still makes them waste a battle phase and saves you from a potential OTK that turn). I also added in Underworld Goddess of the Closed World from Blazing Vortex. This is also just an amazing card to out boss monsters that "can't be destroyed by card effects/battle and can't be targeted" (Dragoon/Borrelend/etc.), and she has a pretty nice effect too.  Also just wanted to put it out there because I sometimes forget: but if the opp. has monsters like Barrier Statue of the Stormwinds or Vanity's Ruler, you can use Archfiend Eccentrick to destroy them.

deck_name: Tier 1 Dragon Link - Combos + Decklist NEW META 2021
deck_description:
Hello and welcome to yet another (you guessed it!) Dragon link build!! Dragon link stays strong and is still one of the best decks of the format. Some decks like Drytron, Virtual World and Zoo-Eldlich are clearly better but dragon link is not out of the game yet. A mere linkross ban cannot keep this deck from going down tiers. If I were to rank dragon link in the current metagame, I would give it a solid tier 1.5 (Tier 1 would be Drytron, VW and Eldlich). Another thing to consider is that Dragon link Took 1st in the 3v3 LCS 10!! There were more than 300 players participating in this tournament and dragon link still found it’s way to the top (Insert Sam saying “I TOLD YOU!!!” Here). 1st place was taken by Gabriel Netz and his team and this build I have today is inspired off of his build but has differences.    Before Doing the deck explanation, I just wanted to thank everyone here at YGOPROdeck for all the support. This is deck #30 for me and I have already hit over 115,000 total views for my decks here on YGOPROdeck!! To me this means a lot and I feel like it is amazing being able to communicate with so many people. Thanks for the support!   Just a quick reminder that the deck explanation, All the combos and explanations on ways to best use your resources are ALL on my Youtube video. Subscribing to the channel would be a great way to support me and the channel!   Link to the video - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dxoVkis44ng   Changes I am making to my build (compared to my older versions) - 
    1. I am not playing VFD - this is not a deck revolving around using VFD as the main negate/win condition. It uses several different kinds of interruptions to disrupt the opponent. It uses specific interruptions designed to counter the top tier decks of the current metagame. For example, Heradic seal and Dragonmaid Tidying are used to bounce back cards to the opponent’s hand - this is an amazing way to counter Zoodiac (very reliant on normal summon) and Virtual world (gets rid of the card targets for the VW monsters) and is also a high impact interruption which can be used to get rid of walls like Dragoon and Final Sigma as well (bounce does not target or destroy) and Number 68 completely exodia obliterates Drytron and is also effective against eldlich and other graveyard reliant decks. 
    2. I am playing a 40 card deck - To increase consistency this was needed. This deck is also not playing bricks (except PSY-Driver which does not count) so it is completely ok to play 40 cards because the main reason Dragon link played bricks in the first place was to reduce the risk of drawing bricks, but since this deck plays only 1 brick, it is fine to play 40. The 1st place deck also played 40 cards.
 
  • I am not running black metal - Again, I needed to make the deck 40 cards and there wasn’t space for this. Also, since decks like Drytron are in the metagame, the popularity of skull mister is gone up and Black metal is a skull mister target. I just felt like Seyfert and Chaos space were more than enough. Seyfert and space also have the protection of GAMMA.
  • I am running Chamber Dragonmaid and Dragonmaid Tidying - This was because Tidying is such a strong trap and is very high impact. Chamber can serve as the normal summon and since the deck just plays so many extenders, the deck can afford to play Chamber as a normal summon instead of something like seyfert. Normal summoning Chamber is better than normal summoning something like rokket tracer. Chamber can also be summoned off of elpy if not drawn. Tidying also serves as a monster reborn for the following turn and that will allow chamber to search another tidying if you need to play the grind game.
    Composition of the deck -  
Starters (cards you usually normal summon to get the combo going - there are ones that do not require the normal summon but almost all the starters get you into a romulus) For starters (get it? Starters? Nvm) I am playing 3 Chamber Dragonmaid, 3 Seyfert, 3 Chaos Space, 1 Black Dragon and 1 White Dragon. Chamber does not get you into a romulus and requires an extra extender to work with but is a great card since it increases the disruptions on the endboard by 1 in the form of a very high impact trap card - Dragonmaid tidying. This is well worth the extender and chamber is also something’s summoned off of elpy. Seyfert and chaos space (the best starter) are to search the chaos dragons and can be protected from ash blossom with gamma. If one of the chaos dragons are drawn, with any normal summon of the other attribute (light or dark) it is basically a starter on its own. Chaos space can also search lavineer and if you manage to not banish seyfert, you can even mill lavineer with ravine, use seyfert to add back lavineer and search anything else with Brotaur!!
Extenders (cards that extend your plays and help if you get hit with handtraps) The extenders are - 3 Quick launch, 3 World Legacy, 3 Noctovision, 1 brotar and 1 Lavineer. No explanation needed for those, all of those will help you extend plays.
Combo extenders (cards that extend your combo, put up additional disruptions and are good to see in hand but cannot help you if you get handtrapped in most cases) They are - 3 Tracer, 2 synchron, 1 recharger, 1 absorouter and 2 Tidying. All of these cards help your plays and combos in setting additional interruptions - watch my video for knowing how these help the combo, you need to actually know the combo to understand why these cards help.
Handtraps I am running 3 ash and 3 gamma, very self explanatory.
Soft Bricks They are (one each) PSY-Driver, Boot Sector and Dragon Ravine. Soft bricks simply mean a -1, nothing too dangerous.
  Cards in this deck that counter the current meta -   Notice that cards from the side deck are also included. The stuff in parenthesis is what the card counters in that deck, if there is no parenthesis, it means it counters the deck in general. Ash is not in this list since it counters literally everything. Basic interruptions such as seal, savage, and tidying are not mentioned unless they specifically counter a certain deck - they also counter literally anything but I choose not to add them in. And yes Tri-brigade and rocks are meta now.   
  1. Drytron - number 68 (hardcounter), droll (hardcounter), nibiru, droplet (ruler and ultimateness)
  2. Eldlich - hfd and cosmic cyclone (backrow removal), lancea (side deck), lavineer (can pop backrow), unchained (pops) and basic removal cards, number 68
  3. Zoodiac (all to counter zeus) - dinowrestler, kaijus, nibiru, droplet, tidying and seal (zoo is very relient on normal summon)
  4. Virtual World - droplet (VFD and shenshen), gamma(VFD), cosmic cyclone (banishes chuche - makes them unable to combo), nibiru (not always useful since number 75 is in VW), seal and tidying (get rid of the targets for the VW monsters), kaiju (shenshen), dinowrestler (shenshen), droll, lancea 
  5. Bird up! Tri-Brigade - droplet (apex avian and zeus), lancea (hardcounter), kaijus and dinowrestler (zeus and apex avian), nibiru, seal and tidying (relient on certain combo pieces to resolve)
  6. Adamancipators - nibiru, droplet (for the multiple negate endboard), kaijus and dinowrestler (break endboard), tidying and seal (fairly relient on normal summon)
  Conclusion - Dragon link is a solid meta contender and I would rank it (in the current metagame) a tier 1.5 deck. It is definitely not the best deck or anything, in my opinion Drytron, Virtual World and Eldlich outrank it (tier 1 decks) but Dragon link is still a great meta choice. If you want to win more, I would recommend playing one of the other 3 decks but Dragon link can also win duels - just that the other 3 decks are a little better. If you are like me you would play dragon link anyway!! The deck can easily go anti meta and fares fairly well against the top 3 meta contenders but loses easily to NIBIRU. I think in the end it all comes down to how familiar you are with the deck, if you are confident and familiar with this deck - I saw go for it beat all the other meta contenders and show them who’s on top!!! Dragon link best deck lets goooo!   Just a quick reminder that the deck explanation, All the combos and explanations on ways to best use your resources are ALL on my Youtube video. Subscribing to the channel would be a great way to support me and the channel!   Link to the video - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dxoVkis44ng   Also make sure to answer the poll question in the comments! Today’s poll question is: If you had to rank all the yugioh anime, what order would you rank them and what score would you give each of them out of 10?   Mine would be -
  1. 5ds (9.5/10)
  2. ZEXAL (9/10)
  3. Duel monsters season 1 (8/10)
  4. Vrains (7/10)
  5. Duel academy (7/10)
  6. Arc - v (1/10)
  Thanks and I’ll see you next time!! :D

deck_excerpt: "I could've sworn my deck was right here" - my opponents
deck_description: The Strategy of this deck is to mill your opponent's deck entirely with Soul-Absorbing Bone Tower. So how does this deck achieve it's goal? devote the entire thing to specialing zombie monsters. What archetype can shit out zombie monsters like it's nobody's business? Mayakashi, specifically the synchro cards + Dakki. Dakki is a tuner that special summons itself from the graveyard when used for a synchro summon. but with practically no protection that either of these cards have, this is where Zombie World comes in. You see, Bone Tower doesn't specify YOU summoning a zombie monster, but EITHER PLAYER. Zombie World, the field spell that turns every monster on both fields and graveyards zombie type essentially limits how many summons your opponent can do before milling their entire deck themselves.

deck_excerpt: The fearsome Kaijus want to destroy everything in their path, but our Heroes will defeat them to save the city.
deck_description: Well here I bring you the deck that I promised you, HERO KAIJU!!! DESTROY THE CITY TO SAVE THE CITY!!! There is not much to say, it is a strange and perhaps unnecessary combination but hey I thought about it because of the concept of Kaijus vs Heros and in the end hey it works it is not spectacular but it works, you have fun and you confuse people. KAIJUS Big boys: Thunder King and Dogoran are normally used to summon them and kick butts or to save the little ones and their negations Little boys: Gameciel and Kumongous easily tribute enemys or you can keep them and have a negation (HERO has no negations :1) Interrupted Kaiju Slumber: You all know the power of this card, you take away the easy field, you settle in with the Kaijus you want and also look for the next turn Kyoutou Waterfront: Needed on anything Kaiju based HERO!!! Well I promise to do this, I think that an explanation of everything HERO is unnecessary since I think it is common knowledge to know how they work and if not, they are tremendously intuitive Honest Neos: Extra ATK Malicious: Go easy to GY and look for another Faris-Vyon-Increase: Easy Combo just with Faris in hand Adusted: Searchable search engine Stratos: Incredibly good card from HERO Liquid Soldier: Good draw ability, in addition to being part of Absolute Zero Solid Soldier: Extra Body Shadow Mist: Great card, can search in any sense Emergency Call: Search for any Elemental (Usually Stratos) Dark Calling: Summon Malicious Bane Miracle Fusion: Sunrise card, in addition to summoning Zero normally Mask Change: Access to all Masked HERO Malicious Bane: Adusted makes him so easy to summon and he's also a monster of destruction. Escuridao: Take off dark stuff Absolute Zero: He is a great hero, easy to summon, destroys field Trinity: He win games Sunrise: Help your heroes, look for Miracle Fusion and it is also easy to summon Masked Acid: Combo with Absolute Zero to clean field Masked Dark Law: One of the best Heroes Masked Blast: Something niche but it works many times Xtra Dread Decimator: Although it may not seem like it, it is easy to summon, in addition to helping the OTK Xtra Wonder Driver: Extend combos Xtra Cross Crusader: With malicious it is easy to invoke in addition to looking for any necessary HERO Other Things Triple Tactics: Very good versatility Polymerization: Vyon card Reinforcement: ROTA Terraforming: Search the kaiju field Reborn: Super Staple Exciton Knight: It's not necessary at all, I just like it :) Unicorn and Phoenix: Best Generic Links Other Options Kaiju: Jizukiru is a good Big Boy and Anti-Kaiju makes the deck even more Kaiju Destiny: Destiny Fusion + Drawhand + Malicious = Dystopia, is a good combo unfortunately you can only play dark, which breaks all this but hey, if you like it you can add Radian to help... oh and Dynatag helps... sometimes HERO: Dian helps Solid Soldier to stand out, in addition to perhaps increasing the copies of him, Favorite Hero synergizes well with the deck through the kaiju field, but in the end I did not like it, although it is a very good option, Form Change to greedy plays Super Poly: The Superpoly Engine is quite good although I am still not convinced Staples: Called is hell of a card and Droplet helps OTK or negations normally Thing you should Know Think well which Kaiju you want to use to tribute and which one to keep, this could decide the. Normally Wonder Driver is in most HERO recipes, because it is quite good but if you are not a great HERO player or a great combo planner you will hardly ever use it so in that case it would be fine to change it Speaking more of the other options, the Superpoly Engine is seriously good, it fits good with the deck and it can also make the Kaijus take advantage even when you gave them to the rival, on the other hand Favorite HERO is great on the deck I mean it with the field, with the other attack that is very good,only that something in me does not finish seeing it, even so I think that the indicated thing would be to be able to the card in the deck to 2 copies. Abhyss: Well maybe I lied about the sphinx, in the end I did not like it but haha memories instead this new archetype of Reptiles... well I will only say that in this one if I have a couple of ideas. Galaxy Control: It sounds crazy but when I saw some cards of the archetype I liked the idea, even so I continue in that because of my low knowledge of the archetype (By the way I think that more than Galaxy is Photon, what should i call the deck?) True Draco Crystal: I continue with the idea of the Deck, it is already done but its a little lazy even so, the most probably thing is that I will upload it soon. Remake of the Best Fusion Deck: Well, the Remake goes there, the bad thing is that it doesn't really add anything good, but that's fine, it's not like I have to change the deck completely. The important thing is to bring it back and explain why is a good deck.   If you would like to see one of this deck, dont forget to comment and share

deck_excerpt: Dragonmaid link combo deck with the rokket engine.
deck_description:
Update : Small changes to the list + adding a replay   Edit : https://www.duelingbook.com/replay?id=447320-26191328 A replay to show the combo and where we can go with it.   Well I assume you are here to look at one of the endless versions of Dragonmaid decks. Its the reason why this archtype became a fan favorite since its launch. You can play controll, stun, combo, 40 cards, 60 cards. Throw pots in, or throw them out ones you see that there is no money left after buying 3 Hospitality. Orrrr you are here for the waifus. Hey I dont judge, aslong as we agree that Drident is best maid. Lets go over it card by card and talk about the goal we have with this deck. The dragonmaid core : 3 Chamber : Searches you the fusion spell, hospi to extend, tidying to extend if you have ravine or to set for controll. She is one of the 1 card sphere maker and what is really important, she is the only one able to summon the fusion maids from grave at the start of the bp. 3 Parlor : Basically works the same as chamber and does almost all the same. Only difference she can send tidying directly for combo, but cant gets its controll eff. However if you already have extender in hand she is a good way to get nurse or any other maid you may need later to grave. Also a 1 card sphere 1 Kitchen : Just a free monster send or if you are lucky and have a big maid in hand which bricks you, also another way to get a new starter like chamber or parlor to hand. Sometimes you may hear a bell ring that you should play none. But look at her and tell me you dont want to have atleast one around. 1 Nurse : She is one of the cards holding the deck together. Overworked nurses are sadly also part in a fantasy card game, thats why you want to use her every turn to extend and summon more maids. She is basically a flat +1 or +2 everytime you summon her ones the grave is set. 2 Changeover : Your fusion spell to go into the gem of the deck Dragonmaid Sheou/Strahl, or House when you are lead down the dark path of VFD. Important to remember for the gy effect, even if the target leaves the board, you still add changeover to hand. 3 Hospitality : Probably one of the most broken extender to ever be printed. Set up your grave, non target summon from hand and gy. Searchable and one activation a turn no use. Sadly the price tag is justified, but dont buy it if you can avoid. Dont let people sky rock the price and gate people out. the reprint is coming ! 3 Tidiyng : Looping cards back to hand and in best case triggering your House is always good, but non target summon from hand or gy in etiher players turn while being searchable by two cards ? This card should be the 40$ one~   Rokket : 2 Tracer : Its tracer, it summons another rokket for a free Chaos ruler or Savage Dragon, and can be summoned by quick launch. Yeah, I dont know how quick launch and this can exist at the same time. 2 Absoruter : As we play Ravine we love discarding things that also give us free cards back so this card is already good for us, but it can also work as a mini noctovision dragon if we have a rokket on board. Dragon, free summon and search? Sign me up 1 Silver : Wont come up often but the banish eff can be nice 1 Recharger : target for quicklaunch and tracer, but also can work with striker dragon eff to recycle a tracer back to hand and summon 2 of boot sector
  1. Boot Sector : Summon striker, search this spam rokkets. Simple
Dragons : Noctovision : Make striker = free summon. Simple. gives you a extra draw and protects your set tidying when in grave, this card is basically a dragonmaid. Since its release its been probably the most played card which isnt part of the archtype. Odd-eyes : High level dragon for fusion, which can search Emperor who we talk about in a bit. Can also summon fusion Monster from grave, and in 1 of a Million, can set up a pendulum scale. Its fun to use but can be cut. Emperor : Recycles your banished dragons , is a high level dragon for fusion and can nuke the board in emergencys when you need non target removal. If you cut odd-eyes also cut this one 3 Nibiru : Big rock vs combo deck go token 3Gamma and 1 Driver : One of the strongest hand traps in the game with only little downside. You can use it to stop the opponent of going full combo or you can use it in your turn to protect a search spell / stop vfd / Zexel. And if you can do it in your turn you also get a free Chaos ruler. I see that as a absolute win. 1 Miradora : Situational and not to good currently. But we can search it of Tempest + its a high level dragon for fusion. 1 Dragons Ravine : Search of Romulus and dumb extender and send extender. 1 Tempest 1 Gold Sako : Simple combo to search Miradora or Parlor All in all this deck is just learning which card leads to which combo, but the end board you should aim for is usually Sphere + Sheou or ones you know the cards a little better you can end on Borrel Savage + Sphere + Sheou + Rampage/ Vfd If wanted I can later add a few replays to show combos and how the deck performs against meta / ranked on DB

deck_excerpt: my Unchained build for the February 2021 format
deck_description: So this is my Unchained build fro the February 2021 format. It's sooooo budget, but you can extend it by adding Underworld Goddess of the Closed World. Here I will show you the 2 main combos for the strategy. The first combo is only by having Unchained Twins - Aruha and any Unchained spell/trap - the set card is destroyed and you special summon Aruha - you trigger the set card's floating effect to special summon Unchained Twins - Sarama from your deck - use Sarama's effect, targeting the spell/trap in your GY - that card is set to your field then you destroy Sarama - Sarama's floating effect special summons Abominable Unchained Soul (you can trigger it's effect if you want) - link the 2 monsters you have on the field into Unchained Soul of Rage Now you have a Link-2 monster on your field, who can link itself with an opponents monster during their Main Phase. The second combo, which is an OTK if your opponent has no monsters on their field adn nothing in response to attacks, requires Unchained Twins - Aruha, Unchained Twins - Rakea and any Unchained spell/trap. - you set the spell/trap - pop it with Aruha which is then special summoned - the set card's floating effect triggers to special summon Sarama - normal summon Rakea and proceed to Battle Phase - attack with them for 4500 damage - activate the quick effect of Rakea to pop your Aruha - aruha's floating effect triggers, special summoning Abominable Unchained Soul - it's effect triggers, discarding the card that you have in your hand to pop your Sarama (or Rakea, it doesn't        matter)   - it's floating effect triggers to special summon one of your Unchained monsters (doesn't matter which) and swing for game So that's all for the combo tutorial, good luck!

This is the 2016 Synchron Build I played back then. The whole point in this deck is to get out 3 negates and possibly a disruption. Only down side is no "monster reborn" or "pot of aiverice" during that time (April 11, 2016 banlist/format)/ With a multitude of combo-lines, adaptability, consistency, and low investments for high rewards; synchrons are full of fair yet broken plays and boards that (for the time) was really hard to out. Making a Quasar and maybe even another piece of interaction, to outright mind gaming your opponent with 1 hand trap (Maxx "C") made some games not even last past turn 1. This deck is my personal build I played with for my locals in my area at the time. I was considered a degenerate player for summoning 4 negates at one point. In this deck, you will find a somewhat irregular choice of main deck, extra and even side which was crafted to take on what I was dueling against on a regular basis where I was. Over all, this is a casual deck, that loves negations and hates being graveyard locked. Your game-plan is a tad linear with almost all your combos starting the same exact way and is easily telegraphed. In modern time, this deck would need to chew through multi-negates, disruptions and even possibly a Nibiru. This deck is not to be taken overly seriously, but on a casual level with friends, could fetch you a game or two.

deck_name: My Witchcrafter deck ( Uses banned cards)
deck_excerpt: Verre+ Spell  chronicles= That snobish little brat
deck_description: Hello everyone, after the Madolche deck I took a break to write guides for my deck  but… I’m back to another cringe idea, so… today it’s time to  Witchcrafters!!! This is a total casual build (Spellbook of Judgment is banned for a reason), made for fun and intent to use for fun, I’m not responsible for any friendship lost by this deck.   Witchcrafter,  Artificers of magic!! The Witchcrafter archetype is adorable in all artwork that is presented, linking the lore of the spellcaster universe ( Endymion, Spellbook, Invokeds), making a third force to  balance power between them. They don't store knowledge like  Prophecy-Spellbook or  use knowledge for power and war like Endymion, instead they use for  (like the name says) craft magic artefacts  that which one of the Witchcrafter are responsible for one process (pottery , glass, jewelry, etc). Enough about them, let’s get into the deck.   Main deck Monsters:   3x Witchcrafter Schmietta:  every low level  Witchcrafter has the effect which she can tribute herself, then  discard a spell card to summon any Witchcrafter from the deck. What  makes Witchcrafter Schmietta unique is the ability to send any Witchcrafter card, in special Witchcrafter Patronus for crazy combos later on.   3x Witchcrafter Genni: Genni was the “glue” that this deck was lacking.The effect that she banished herself with another Witchcrafter spell card to use this effect again… it’s crazy.   2x Witchcrafter Pittore: Pittore is very risky but with so many Witchcrafter spell cards in theis deck, I think this is enough.   1x Witchcrafter Potterie: She does absolutely nothing ‘cause Witchcrafter spell cards can recover from the  GY by themself, but … man… she is adorable lol.   2x Witchcrafter Golem Aruru: a beefie Hand trap, the ability to bounce any opponent’s monster  or recover a  Witchcrafter  spell card and with 2800 ATK it’s even more juicy.   2x Witchcrafter Haine: Can pop a face up card   1x Witchcrafter Edel: Edel was more useful in the past, but today with  Witchcrafter Unveiling is no longer escential, nevertheless is a good beater.   1x Witchcrafter Mademe Verre: The favorite snob loli, this little brat it’s  an Inferno (i’m cursing in my native language). She can negate a face up monster by discarding a spell card, boost a spellcaster by  1000 ATK for which  different spell card in your hand, combos with Spell Chronicle and Witchcrafter Patronus…  Now I know why she looks so snobbish in the artwork.   Spell cards   2x Witchcrafter Holiday: Every spell card of this archetype returns for the player hand if weren’t used in this turn, and of course has an additional unique effect.This card is basically  a monster reborn for the archetype.    3x Witchcrafter Unveiling: Special summons any Witchcrafter from your hand, the department  that was lacking in this deck.    3x Witchcrafter Creation: Search any Witchcrafter monster from your deck   1x Witchcrafter Scroll: Can make you draw a card if your  Witchcrafter monster destroys another monster by attack.     1x Witchcrafter Collaboration: Makes your monster punch a second time, with Witchcrafter Mademe Verre  effect… this is kind of interesting.   1x Witchcrafter Bystreet: Protects your monster for one destruction.   1x Witchcrafter Draping: a Mystical Space Typhoon on steroids, bouncing any spell/trap card up the number Witchcrafter you control.   2x Spellbook of Judgment: It’s banned for a reason, this card is outrageous, can make you go +4 with the right setup and bring any Spellcaster monster  (on in our case, any Witchcrafter monster) up to the number of Spellbooks added to your hand. I hope this card never comes back to the game… that's because it’s so awesome!!   2x Spellbook of Secrets: search any spellbook card.   1x Spellbook of Power: boost the attack of your monster and can search any spellbook card if this monster destroys another monster for battle.   2x Spellbook of Knowledge: a draw card for spellcaster type monster, can even put some GY setup for future plays and a materia folder for Spellbook of Judgment.   1x Spellbook of  Wisdom: Protection for you spellcaster and a materia folder for Spellbook of Judgment.   3x Spell Chronicle: This is an honorable Witchcrafter  card. The effect that banishes any 5 spell card from your deck, and later can be brought to your hand by the effect of  Witchcrafter Patronus and potentially making a 3+ card advantage … is insane. Combos with  Witchcrafter Mademe Verre, Witchcrafter Haine, Witchcrafter Edea, just an incredible teck.   Trap cards   2x Witchcrafter Patronus: the effect that matters is the GY one. Banishing itself to add to you handy  any Witchcrafter card with different names from your banishment pile… is insane if you consider you are running  Spell Chronicle in this deck.   Extra Deck   The extra deck is more kind of a tool to deal with the unknown, so  I’ll not discuss it. Your main play is on the main deck.   Conclusion A very fun waifu deck , with so many options and so insane plays.. I know that are not a very strong deck … but come on Potterie is so cute. I hope you enjoy  it.

deck_excerpt: Use a tight Shiranui and Shaddoll engine to OTK your opponent.
deck_description: What do Shiranui do? Shiranui are an older zombie Synchro archetype. Their primary goal is to use their banishing effects combined with zombies inherent graveyard synergy to OTK the opponent. This Variant opts to go second to take advantage of shiranui’s OTK playstyle and use powerful cards such as Ghost Meets Girl – A Shiranui’s Story and the new Laval Salamander. The deck also uses A small Shaddoll engine as a method to send cards such as Mezuki, Gozuki, or a Shiranui combo piece to grave. Extenders General Advice for playing the deck can be given as follows: Make Lavalval Salamander as often as possible ass he is both the decks best extender and functions as removal. Hold the effects that lock you into summoning only zombies until as late into the combo as possible (ie: Ghost Meets Girl – A Shiranui’s Story, Shiranui Spectralsword Shade, Shiranui Squire). Shaddoll Fusion is an extra spell that lets you set up combos and give your cards protection. By sending Shaddoll Hedgehog and Mezuki to grave you can summon El Shaddoll Shekhinaga which can convert a spell resolving to a free monster negate and draw with an extender in grave. The most basic Shiranui Play is to summon Shiranui Solitare, Tribute Solitare, summon Uni-Zombie use Uni-Zombie to send Mezuki to the graveyard banish Mezuki from the graveyard to summon back Shiranui Solitare from the grave. Then use the two monsters to make a level 8 or 7 synchro. This is the core combo for a lot of other Shiranui combos and this combo is used in ost zombie decks. Shiranui Spiritmaster provides an additional special summon to get out more shiranui’s on board, but more importantly it provides a banishing outlet for what ever you special summon using its effect. For example, if you summon Shiranui Solitare off of Shiranui Spiritmaster’s effect you can perform the basic Shiranui Solitare combo tributing Shiranui Spiritmaster instead to have Shiranui Solitare’s when banished effect live for later. Gozuki is one of the best combo extenders. He can be sent off of Uni-zombie to banish a zombie in grave to summon a zombie in hand, while also functioning as a Uni-zombie on field.  Shiranui Spectral Shade is a final extender as it locks you into zombies but provides insane recursion.  Fun to note Gold Sarcophagus triggers any Shiranui’s banish effect. It can be a destroy one, Summon a banished or a draw one discard one. The Math and Consistency 73.57% chance to open at least one handtrap. 82.00% for at least one starter and extender ~93.54% chance for at least one starter Extra Deck The relevant Shiranui Package consists of Shiranui Sunsaga, Shiranui Shogunsaga, Shiranui Squiresaga, and last and least Shiranui Samuraisaga. Shiranui Shogunsaga and Shiranui Squiresaga are the two main OTK Enablers and extenders, both banish a card to gain attack. Shiranui Sunsaga, lets you reset your banished or in grave zombie synchro monsters for some removal while grandting protection. Shiranui Samuaisaga is only run as a target for Shiranui Spectralsword, its not good and should only be used as a forced steppingstone. This package lets the player grind out games as the Shiranui engine loops itself very well. Lavalval Salamander is insane Shiranui support and you can’t convince me otherwise. He draws you two cards and then puts two in grave. He banishes your Shiranui monsters in grave for removal. The other synchro monsters and XYZ monsters are situational tools. Tornado Dragon is for spell and trap removal. Psy-framelord Omega is crazy in grindy games. Number 41: Bagooska the Terribly Tired Tapir is a backup plan for going first. Lastly, Beelze of the Diabolic Dragon is a great pressure tool for decks that struggle with non-destruction removal. The zombie link package is mostly for extending off of cards such as Shiranui Spectralsword Shade and Shiranui Squire. Its also generic link value for zombies. The Shaddoll extra deck package just covers all the possible options for what you could need. El Shaddoll Shekhinaga is the recommended choice. Side Deck             Ironically the side deck is mostly used for going first. Shiranui Style Swallow’s Slash is an insane stuttered pop 3 that can mess with your opponent’s timings. By destroying two then banishing Shiranui Spiritmaster to pop another, your opponent can be left at severe disadvantage. Trap Trick helps get Shiranui Style Swallow’s Slash out but can also get Infinite Impermanence. Macro Cosmos and Dimensional Fissure might seem counter intuitive but if they are used after you set up going first they have little effect on you compared to the dramatic stun effect they have on the opponent. Psy-framelord Omega is crazy here. Imperial Order works similarly. Nibiru, the Primal Being helps control combo decks. Red Reboot stops Trap decks. Harpies Feather Duster helps stop backrow deck. Called by the Grave helps stop handtraps going first.

deck_description: Write your deck strategy here...ewvds

I am ecstatic for the new Stardust support  and I really like how they decided to bolster the power of the existing Majestic support. The deck functionally goes first since Stardust has many options to put up negates nowadays. You can get a pretty good endboard with a two card combo of just Junk Converter and Stardust Synchron. But you will get more out of it if you have Doppelwarrior as well. Main Deck includes 3 Ash Blossom, 3 Quickdraw Synchron, 3 Stardust Synchron, 1 Stardust Trail, 3 Junk Synchron, 3 Junk Converter, 3 Doppelwarrior, 1 Stardust Xiaolong, and 1 Wish-Converging Dragon. Quickdraw Synchron is just Tzolkin fodder and I guess you can use it as a target for Shooting Riser Dragon if you decide to play things like Shooting Star Dragon, Stardust Warrior, or Satellite Warrior. Stardust Synchron is a level 4 Synchron tuner which is very good already and it searches basically most of your much needed Spells/Traps, but its sad that it doesn't search Synchro Chase but that is understandable. If you discard it off of Converter, its essentially a free extender from grave. Stardust Trail is a decent card since it is a level 4 extender, but its the primary target for Stardust Illuminate other than Xiaolong. Junk Synchron is bonkers of course. Junk Converter is grave set-up, a searcher, and it gives you an extender. Doppelwarrior is just here since it makes tokens. Xiaolong is another Illuminate target. Wish-Converging Dragon gets you to Majestic Star and Shooting Majestic Star. Spells and Traps aren't surprising. 3 Tuning. 3 Stardust Illuminate which is a Foolish and level modulation. 3 Synchro Chase since it makes sure your effects go through. 1 ROTA. 1 Reborn. 3 Arriving Miracle which is just to get you to your Majestic monsters. 1 Called By since every play in this deck is just asking to be handtrapped. 2 TTT for the same reason. 1 Black Garden to either go with Garden Rose Maiden or Garden Rose Flora. Finally, 1 Majestic Mirage since it essentially makes your Shooting Majestic Star Dragon's 1 negate into 3 interruptions. Extra Deck. 1 Ultimaya Tzolkin since it brings out either Moonlight or Crystal Wing. 2 Shooting Majestic Star Dragon which is an interruption going first and your OTK enabler going second. 1 Blood Rose Dragon since its a thing going second or you can take something like 1 of your Junk Speeders out and replace it with a normal Black Rose Dragon to use Blood Rose's second effect as another form of disruption probably. 1 Majestic Star Dragon which is just insane and it doesn't need to return to the ED if you have Arriving Miracle face-up. 1 Crystal Wing Synchro Dragon and 1 Blackrose Moonlight Dragon as Tzolkin targets. 1 of the original Stardust Dragon and 1 Stardust Spark Dragon. 1 Stardust Charge Warrior. 1 T.G. Hyper Librarian. 2 Junk Speeder. 1 Garden Rose Flora which is just Tzolkin fodder and a thing for Blood Rose, but you can switch it for Accel Synchron if you value the level modulation. Finally, 1 Garden Rose Maiden which is more Tzolkin fodder and it revives a Dragon Synchro from grave. It also searches Black Garden which can be used as an extender of sorts. Side Deck is meh. 2 Nibiru. 3 Belle. 3 Majestic Absorption which is really only here for the equip effect going second. 3 Lightning Storm. 2 Forbidden Droplet. 2 Starlight Road because its a Stardust deck so why not.

deck_excerpt: An control deck that utilises the abhyss cards alongside the lair cards.
deck_description:
This is a (Prototype)version of an Abhyss deck that utilises the lair cards. Some key cards
  1. Lair of Darkness: The key card, it enables the deck to function properly, so this needs to hit the field asap.
  2. Ahrima, the wicked warden: Lair searcher, can also serve as an searcher for some of the dark monsters in the deck.
  3. Lilith, lady of lament: searches the traps, as well as an quick-play monster removal.
  4. The virus traps: one of the centrepieces of this deck, to lock off opponents.
  5. Darkest Diabolos, lord of the lair: One of the bosses of the deck, easily summons itself from practically anywhere(except from the deck), due to the high-level abhyss monster's effect, or from the virus traps and the other lair monsters.
  6. The abhyss bosses: 1 copy of deity, 1 copy of king and queen, 1 copies of dawn and dusk to enable rank 8 plays, link plays, as well as just using them for their nice effects(deity can non destruction remove all monsters on the field that wasnt summoned from the gy, king and queen can send a card from the opponents field and hand each time a monster(s) is(are) summoned from their gy(synergises with the other abhyss monsters), dawn and dusk enables the rank 8 plays, as well as comboing well with the effects of king and queen(dawn adds a monster from the opponents gy to their hand, but the virus cards can easily take care of them)(Curse summons a monster from the opponents gy, but king, queen, and the virus cards can take care of them, as well as the lair cards.)

deck_excerpt: Abuse Junk Speeder and the new Majestic Dragon Support
deck_description:
First let me tell you this deck is still a WIP (need to cut a few cards) But now let me sell you on why this is the best way to play the Majestic support As far as I know there are 4 approaches to this that I have seen
  1. Assault mode
  2. Dragon Link
  3. Speeder (mine)
  4. Speeder but different
Assault mode has a similar idea to my approach, add an engine to get an extra negate. However by itself it does much less, and also you have to hard draw more pieces of the majestic support to get that combo going Dragon link is not really using the support so I don't like it. Different speeder, in my opinion might be the better way to approach it. The goal of my deck is end on a few monsters that interupt your opponent but come back after their turn so that you can reccur advantage. Different speeder focuses much more on turboing negates to the field and opressing your opponent so they can't even put you behind. Those decks generally use Ultimaya Tzolkin, Hot Red Dragon Archfiend Abyss, etc. You can add some of those elements to this deck by adding Quickdraw Synchron, tzolkin, and abyss, and probably take out Double Star Shaman and Cosmic Blazar Dragon. But without further ado, my approach. Buckle up, it's a long ride. There are several branches, so I will talk about the main combos the deck has. First of all the keystone of the deck, Junk Speeder. The easiest way to summon it is with Junk Synchron and a lv 2 in grave (setup by Junk Converter) or sometimes Synchron Carrier + Junk Synchron or Synchron Carrier + Cyberse Synchron (cyberse synchron effect on carrier) I will cover the other easiest way to setup the first lv 2 in grave later.   NOTE: Always have a monster in the EMZ if you can, it saves space But essentially with speeder you summon every card you can (Cyberse, Satellite Synchron, Junk, Stardust) And then Stardust Synchron can get its search based on what is in your hand right now (In order of importance you search Arriving Miracle, Majestic Mirage, Stardust Illuminate, Majestic Absorption) - only search absorption if you need to out a card or are going for game   Assuming you have nothing good in hand, stardust synchron searches arriving Activate the arriving and stack wish-converging dragon Next, synchro summon Red Supernova Dragon with Junk speeder, stardust synchron, satellite, and cyberse (5+4+2+1=12) Arriving draws a card, special summoning wish-converging who can special summon Omni Dragon Brotaur Upon special summoning, Brotaur uses its effect to discard a card, targeting wish converging, add Stardust Trail  Use stardust synchron in grave to tribute junk synchron Use trail in hand to special itself Synchro Stardust Dragon with trail and stardust synchron Trail summons a token here Summon Shooting Majestic Star Dragon using the token, brotaur, wish-converging, and stardust   Thus your end board is 1 negate and 1 board wipe   Now how does this get better? Firstly if you used converter for the setup and used illuminate already to send trail to the graveyard Converter can special summon junk synchron from the grave after you summon junk speeder When your field consists of Red Supernova Dragon, Stardust Dragon, token, wish-converging, brotaur, and junk synchron (extra from converter) Banish illuminate from grave to increase stardust dragon's lv by 1 Summon shooting majestic with Stardust, token, wish-converging Summon Herald of the Arc Light with brotaur and junk synchron Now we got 2 negates and a board wipe! Note: If you didn't use illuminate, instead of banishing illuminate, continue with the combo as normal, but instead of shooting majestic star, summon normal Majestic Star Dragon using the token, stardust dragon, and wish converging, then you can summon herald with brotaur and junk synchron   Now time for that other way to setup the lv 2 The obvious sore thumb in this decklist is petite dragon right? Now comes its use, if you opened junk synchron + dragon shrine you can do the same as the non illuminate variation of the above combo by Activating Dragon Shrine  (send petite dragon first, guardragon promineses second) Normal summon junk synchron, special petite dragon Summon speeder with the two cards Speeder chain link 1, Guardragon chainlink 2 Summon all the tuners from deck (search arriving) Use arriving to stack wish-converging Summon supernova with stardust synchron, satellite, speeder, cyberse Draw with arriving (use wish-converging to summon brotaur, use brotaur on wish-converging to search trail) Stardust Synchron tributes guardragon Trail specials from hand Summon stardust dragon with trail and stardust synchron (trail summons a token) Summon normal majestic star with Stardust, token, wish-converging Summon herald with junk synchron and broataur (Once again, having used illuminate means you can increase stardust dragon's level by 1 and can summon shooting majestic instaed of normal majestic)     Of course if you really want to have the shooting majestic, you can summon it with stardust, token, brotaur, and wish-converging instead of having normal majestic star + herald   I think I should note incase someone doesnt know, Majestic Mirrage lets normal majestic star and shooting majestic star not be once per turn, so it is really good with shooting majestic because it keeps on coming back, but normal majestic star tributes itself permenantly, so after negating once you have to decide if it is worth negating and giving it up permanently   There are many other paths this deck can go down but those are the main things you should keep lines you should keep in mind HALP I GOT HANDTRAPPED: Bait out hand traps with your searchers Hope you have crossout designator, also add the handtraps you are scared of, I only have ash Also, if they stop speeder, you can still do the shooting majestic star combo by tributing speeder for stardust synchron and using trail However, converter can chainblock for speeder to help protect from ash Veiler/Imperm on Junk Synchron or Junk Speeder can be cirucmvented with the majestic combo If you made Speeder with converter and they veiler/imperm speeder, converter summoning back junk synchron lets you go into crystal wing   Why are you playing 43 cards git good: I really should, once again this deck is a wip and I haven't decided which 3 cards to cut   Why is your side deck so weird: These are just cards I considered playing, not an actual side deck, put in cards you feel  are necessary   Where is doppelwarrior: If you are playing the other speeder variant it is probably more needed, but for me it was more of a brick. Whenever I could use its effect it didn't improve my end board by that much.   Why is the extra bad: I started with the base of a synchro deck I had from before jet synchro was banned, so it had some combos based on that. The cards in the extra I would recommend replacing if you want to change stuff up are: Double star shaman Martial Metal Marcher T.G. Hyper Librarian ? Stardust charge warrior Satellite warrior Cosmic Blazar Dragon (That's a worryingly large amount of carsd in retrospect)   Please let me know if you have any comments, any advice is appreciated!

deck_excerpt: Pure Tri-Brigade. Just as good going second as it is going first.
deck_description: Open Fraktall for Simorgh Lock. Use your other 4 cards to make linkuriboh or double dragon lord to protect the barrier statue. You can often also get out Abyss Dweller to make the first turn lock stronger Everything else is free value. You can often play through 3 interruptions (say Ash, Imperm, and Ghost Belle). If you lock your opponent out first turn with barrier statue, you should be able to do lethal if not close to it by the following turn. There are a lot of moving pieces with some interesting chain blocks so the interactions are interesting and the deck's grind game is very good.  One of the best parts is the revolt, which I think is extremely underrated. Use it to bring back nervall, kit, and any of the lower links (usually at least Ferrjit) to link summon Shuraig. This lets you non-target banish, search a tri-brigade, send a tri-brigade, and cycle a card in hand, all off of 1 card. If that doesn't sound too good, note that this comes up very often.

deck_excerpt: Use Frogs to either control the field or build up to Scary Link Monsters (tm).
deck_description: - Use Swap Frog to discard another water monster (anything in this deck, though frogs are preferable) to special summon Swap Frog onto the field without using your normal summon. At this point you can bounce swap frog back to the hand and summon it again. either discarding another monster or using your normal summon. Keep in mind that you can normal summon a frog monster for free after bouncing Swap Frog back to the hand with its effect.  -Try to get a Ronintoadin into the graveyard with a second frog monster. By banishing the second frog monster, Ronintoadin can special summon itself to the field.  -Get Toadally Awesome out as soon as possible. Two level 2 frogs. It gives you card advantage very quickly.  -Use Dupe Frog to stop opponents from attacking anything except for Dupe Frog. Get two Dupe Frogs up to stop the opponent from attacking at all. If a Dupe Frog goes to the graveyard by battle or many effects you can add a frog to your hand from graveyard or Deck. (Dupe frog can "miss the timing," making some effects not allow Dupe Frog to activate at all.)  -Toadally Awesome is at 3 now. You don't have to bounce Toadally back to the Extra Deck after it leaves the field *every* time anymore. Try bouncing Swap Frog back when Toadally Awesome leaves to load your graveyard up with Ronintoadins and Frogs, which you can use to summon more Toadally Awesome's  -Use Sea Lancer to bring your banished frogs back to the field as equip spells. Link summon something using Sea Lancer as material to return these frogs to the graveyard, where Ronintoadin can banish them to special summon itself repeatedly.  -Avoid banishing Swap Frog from your graveyard for Ronintoadin's effect without either a Sea Lancer in your hand to return monsters to your graveyard from the banish zone or unless you really need a frog on the field.  -Transmodify will let you get Swap Frog on the field by sacrificing a level 1 Water/Aqua monster on the field to the graveyard. Using a level 2 Aqua/Water Monster (most frogs), It will also allow you to Special Summon Glacial Beast Polar Penguin, activating its exceedingly rude field removal effect (back to hand), Gora Turtle, which stops anyone from attacking with anything higher than 1900 ATK, or Graydle Alligator, which, when Destroyed by either Spell or Battle, allows you to take control of an opponents monster.  -Salvage Swap Frog and another Frog when it's convenient. Load your graveyard up.  -Build up to Accesscode Talker using link monsters of a lower link level and a single Ronintoadin bouncing itself back to the field repeatedly. This will allow you to give Accesscode Talker a metric shit ton of Link monsters to banish in order to activate its omni-removal effect.

deck_excerpt: This deck utilises the "Digital Bug" archetype in order to create powerful rank 3 xyz in order to disrupt your opponets plays.
deck_description:
This deck utilises the "Digital Bug" archetype in order to create powerful rank 3 xyz in order to disrupt your opponets plays. Your main plan is too summon as many level 3 monsters as possible and xyz into Cicada King and Scaradiator. This deck prefers to go first since it allows it to play with a smaller chance of being disrupted. Detailed analysis of every card: Digital Bug Centibit: One of the Digital Bug cards. You can switch this card to defence position with cards such as stumbling in order to use its effect and go into a rank 3 monster. Very good card to have in your oppening hand if you have stumbling as well. Its xyz effect can allow easy otk's and destruction of the opponets monsters. Digital Bug Websolder: One of the Digital Bug cards. Probably the best one depending on your situation. Its effect allows to special summon any level 3 insect from hand which makes it easy to summon any rank 3. It can also change other Digital Bugs to defence and trigger their effects. Its xyz effect is by far the best one and will give you a major advantage against your opponet. It changes all monsters they control to defence and also makes their attack 0 which makes them easy targets. It also gives you an easy way to summon Mother Spider. Digital Bug Cocoondedenser: One of the Digital Bug cards. This one is great to have in the late game where you will likely have a Digital Bug in your graveyard. Other than that its xyz effect is good in order to counter any battle traps your opponet may have. Digital Bug LEDybug: One of the Digital Bug cards. Its good in order to add cards like Websolder or other combo extenders to hand. Other than that its xyz effect can give you some draw power which is always good. Mirror Ladybug: One of your combo extenders. While you only control one level 3 monster you can special summon this card and make it level 3 in order to summon a rank 3 monster. It is not the best combo extender since it requires for you to have only one monster which will likely only happen during early game however it is still good enough to run at 3 and make the deck more consistent. Battlewasp - Twinbow the Attacker: One of your combo extenders. This one is just insane since you can summon it for free with almost no draw backs and it is a level 3 insect. This card is great to have during any moment in the duel and it is also a good monster to search with LEDybug. Galaxy Worm: All you need to do is normal summon this card and you have a rank 3 xyz. It is a very good card to have during your oppening hand but it can prove to be much less useful during the rest of the game. Kumootoko: Its a level 3 insect normal monster. The only reason you play this at 3 is for Giant Ball Park. You just need to hope you dont draw it and everything will go well. You can also summon it with Giant Ball Park if it is in gy when a monster you control is sent to gy which is a nice addition to its primary effect. Mother Spider: Very good card to ruin your opponets board. It is usually easy to resolve this effect with cards like Websolder and Stumbling so its a great addition to the deck. The only reason I play 1 is because it is a brick during your oppening hand. Speedroid Terrortop: An easy special summoned which will give you a rank 3 xyz. When summoned make sure to add Taketomborg so that you can special summon it and go into a rank 3. Speedroid Taketomborg: A card which you dont want to draw ever. Its only use is being searched with Terrortop and going into rank 3. You can also special summon it if you control Cicada King which makes it more useful. Gokipole: This cards purpose is being sent to gy with Giant Ball Park or foolish burrial so you can add any insect you need at the time. You do not want to draw this. Giant Ball Park: A very strong field spell and great addition to the deck. This card can special summon two Kumootoko's with its effect which gives you access to any rank 3. It can also summon Kumootoko from gy if a monster you control is sent to gy which is a nice effect to have. Stumbling: A very good card to have in this deck since your monsters gain alot of effects from changing their positions. Basically all the you have to do is just summon a card like Digital Bug LEDybug in attack position and then Stumbling will trigger which puts it in defence giving you the effect. It also slows down opponets plays and prevents them from otking you. Bug Signal: You can use this card in order to summon your other xyz monsters. Normally a card like this will not be needed however it can be very useful in times where your opponet has the advantage. You can also activate it when your opponet would destroy an xyz monster you control in order to replace it with another one. Photon Lead: Special summon monsters from your hand to extend comboes. Foolish Burrial: To send Gokipole to gy. Terraforming: To add Giant Ball Park. Digital Bug Scaradiator: An easy negate and also change your opponets battle position. It also attached cards it destroys as materials. You will probably want to summon this after you have summoned Cicada. You can also use it to summon the Digital Bug Corebage. Number 3 Cicada King: The best card in the deck. This shoul be the first xyz you summon. It can negate a monster effect and also summon the insects that it detaches which makes it easy to summon other rank 3 monsters. If you manage to xyz summon this using Digital Bug Websolder then you will have a great advantage. Digital Bug Corebage: Summoned with Digital Bug Scaradiator or Bug Signal. It is good for certain situations. Digital Bug Rhinosebus: You will almost never summon this but it has destruction effect and could be used in situations where you need to kill your opponet fast.
Number 75: Bamboozling Gossip Shadow: This card is great to have since it can practically negate a monster effect and also provides draw power. Inzektron Extra-Stag: Your primary target for Bug Signal since it can easily get rid of your opponets monsters and also remove cards from their gy. Super Quantal Mech Beast Grampulse: Backrow removal. Number 28 Titanic Moth: For the otks. Seraphim Papillon: The only decent link monster for this deck. This card can bring back alot of insects from your gy in order to make rank 3's but it can also be used as a beatstick

deck_excerpt: Special summon Black Rose Dragon every turn or blow up your opponents field during their turn with Blood Rose Dragon!
deck_description:
The goal of the deck is to summon Halqifibrax turn 1 to special summon Red Rose Dragon and use any other level 3 or 4 monster to go into Marjoram or Black Rose Dragon. This sets the field up so that you can go for a Blood Rose Dragon (blow up field) or a Crystal Wing (negate) on your opponents turn using Halqifibrax's second effect to special summon a turner synchro monster such as Formula Synchron or Shooting Riser Dragon. The deck is very consistent at performing this set-up; here are few ways to do so: I: Predaplant Scorpio
  1. Summon Predaplant Scorpio and activate effect to summon Cobra from deck
  2. Cobra adds instant fusion
  3. Activate instant fusion to summon Theseus and go into Halqifibrax to get Red Rose Dragon
  4. Use Red Rose Dragon and left-over Predaplant to go into Marjoram
II: Witch of the Blood Rose and White Rose Dragon or Wheeleder
  1. Summon Witch of the Blood Rose to add Witch of the Black Rose and stack Rose Fairy on top of deck
  2. Summon Witch of the Black Rose to draw Rose Fairy
  3. Rose Fairy activates to special summon itself
  4. Special summon Wheeleder and go into Halqifibrax. Alternativately, make Halqifibrax first, then special summon White Rose Dragon
III: Righty Driver and White Rose Dragon or Wheeleder
  1. Summon Righty Driver to special summon Lefty Driver
  2. Use Lefty Driver's second effect to make itself level 3
  3. Special summon Wheeleder and go into Halqifibrax. Alternativately, make Halqifibrax first, then special summon White Rose Dragon
Lonefire Blossom makes it so you can pull Witch of the Blood Rose or Predaplant Scorpio out of the deck for added consistency. Rose Princess also allows you to save your normal summon to go for a more extended play or bait an Ash Blossom. With any of the set-ups listed above, you can end with 1 negate (Crystal Wing) and 1 pop (Crocodragon,) or 1 pop and 1 field clear (Blood Rose Dragon.) Lefty/Righty Driver can be removed and replaced with Ash Blossoms or other negate cards. The deck struggles going second against multi-negate boards but can put out a very strong turn 1 board.   Deck List:
