deck_excerpt: A pure Lunalight OTK deck. Hope you like it :D.
deck_description:
A pretty simple Lunalight deck without tiger (sadly ._.) that aims to put big numbers on the field that the opponent can't do anything about. The deck mainly follows these rules:
  • Try to get to Leo dancer using monsters on-field/in-hand first, then use wolf to make either panther dancer or sabre dancer, depending on the situation. It's important to banish chick when making that fusion, so you can win uninterrupted.
  • Throw down wolf as soon as possible after baiting negations.
  • Chick dumps either panther dancer or yellow marten for lunalight fusion. This is flexible, you might want to dump butterfly or emerald bird depending on the situation.
  • Emerald bird usually dumps marten if it's in hand, otherwise dumps any monster. You don't want to get rid of a lunalight fusion unless you've already used it that turn, or have drawn into both. The more fusion spells the better since chick/tenyi can create so much advantage.
  • Foolish burial usually dumps serenade dance and not perfume. All flexible, of course. Before getting leo dancer, this deck doesn't have a single linear plan to get there, you just have to use what you drew into.
I've seen some lists that run many blue cat's, but I've found it pretty uncommon to pull it's effect off, so I've decided to run it at one. Same with butterfly, it's effect isn't a necessity for most games. Emerald bird and/or yellow marten can help you go into tiger king, which has come in clutch a couple of times.  I've tried to put reasoning and foolish burial into this deck, but surprisingly have never drawn into them, so that might be something you'd want to put in by dropping an emerald bird if you want. You never really go into your link monsters except predaplant verde, they're just to prepare for different situations as the fusion monsters are the main bosses. I've found infinite impermanence is a great hand trap for this deck, as it also negates a spell/trap, but you can replace it with whatever hand trap you want, of course. Edits:
  • Swapped out blue cat and the crimson foxes for another butterfly, another marten, and have moved the twin twisters to the side deck in favor of three lightning storms. Butterfly accomplishes what fox and cat are trying to do without targeting, and marten can bounce back a pendulum to go into an xyz. Cards like shaddoll schism with non-targeting non-removal can be a real pain.
  • Took out the predaplant fusion for tornado dragon. The lunalights are good enough boss monsters, and tornado dragon is easy to bring out with marten for backrow removal in case you've already used tenki.
  • Took out ghost ogre in favor of alpha in side deck. I'm not sure how kaiju's would be in this deck, I'll test that later.
  • Added alpha into the main deck by taking out a polymerization and a lightning storm. It synergizes pretty well with marten in theory, but I have yet to pull that off in-game. Otherwise, it's a pretty good removal tool.
  • Replaced the alphas missing in the side deck with a crimson fox and a raigeki. You can summon massive 4,000+ monsters and have removal, but if they have an even bigger monster, you surprisingly cannot do anything without crimson fox, so just in case it's there if you need it.
  • Added foolish burial in the main deck. Literally have no idea why I wasn't running it before, it opens up perfume, white rabbit, extra material for wolf, or a free lunalight fusion by dumping marten. Before it would be more difficult to get perfume in the grave, one game I used butterfly on a marten in order to summon it with perfume and get a search, but now it's a lot easier.
  • Discovered the droll & lock bird wasn't in the side deck bc I had the alt artwork in the ydk file, so I added that.

deck_excerpt: Eldlich with Zombie World and Rank 8s
deck_description: Eldlich Deck with Zombie World sprinkles. Negate and banish Monsters with Balerdroch or go into Draglubion to summon your favorite Number-Dragons.  Most of the time you will end first turn with Zombie World, Vampire Sucker and some Traps on the field to then special Balerdroch in your opponents turn from your Graveyard to trigger Sucker and draw. At this point you just start playing Eldlich. Stop for opponent from playing with your favorite traps to then otk your opponent next turn. You can decide if you wanna go the rank 8 Draglubion rout with another Balerdroch to then summon Numero Dragon or go along with Eldlich. But remember! A lot of cards lock you into Zombies. READ the cards before thinking about going into any Ranks.  You can use Rivalery of Warlords and Zombie World to lock your opponent into Zombies after he summoned his first Monster.  Also Scarlet Sanguine lets you summon any Zombie if you already control Golden Lord.        I'm still testing some ratios and would be happy to get some tipps and suggestions especially for Draglubion targets or any other rank 8s that are good :)

deck_excerpt: Patiently waiting for the day that Fossil Machine Skull Convoy gets its TCG release....
deck_description: If you are playing online add 2x Fossil Machine Skull Convoy instead of Skull Bone. Also was not able to add a third Mathematician because of some bug but it's supposed to be in there. Some people might also be asking why Gravedigger's Trap Hole is in here. Well it should be no secret at this point that a lot of monster effects nowadays are activated from the hand and from the graveyard. This is a really cool way to counter handtraps or disrupt a graveyard set up and also to deal some nice damage, which helps you to OTK quicker or might even win the game for you. For an example, when your opponent is clinging to his last couple of life points after a successful battle phase of yours and plans a comeback which involves a combo that either activates a monster effect in the graveyard or the hand (a lot of them do) and then BOOM. Not sure how well this does against tournament decks since I've not been able to try competitive play because of Skull Convoy but I've played against a couple of meta relevant decks and it actually does quite well. Try it out

deck_excerpt: Haz un FTK con el legendario Exodia de la forma más consistente y divertida! Advertencia: Puedes perder amigos UwU. Make an FTK with the legendary Ex
deck_description:
Deck creado por: Darklab Objetivo: Ganar con el efecto de Exodia en el primer turno OwO. Link a la demostración del Deck: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FV4Y33x7nxk Extenders para iniciar el combo:
  • Tour guide from the underworld: Vale x3. Trae al campo a Graff o al Edge imp (el otro lo envías al cementerio usando a Cherubini). En todo caso, es el mejor normal summon del deck.
  • Fiendish rhino warrior: Vale x2. Envía al cementerio el mismo target que la Tour guide, aunque no aprovecha el cuerpo extra. Necesita otro extender sí o sí.
  • Junk forward: Se invoca de modo especial desde la mano si no controlas monstruos, por lo que si lo robas, debe ser el primero en invocarse.
  • Kagemucha knight: Se invoca de modo especial cuando invocas otro monstruo de nivel 3 de modo normal. Ojo que puede perder timing.
  • Psychic wheelder: Se invoca si ya tienes otro monstruo de nivel 3, aunque sólo es una vez por turno.
  • Psychic tracer: Igual que el anterior.
  • Gilasaurus: Se invoca casi gratuitamente. Ojo que el rival puede invocar algo del cementerio, aunque usualmente eso no es un problema.
  • Fossil dig: Trae al Gilasaurus.
  • Foolish burial: Puedes enviar a Cloak para robar a Boots, a costa de no acceder a la ruta no segura; o en su defecto enviar uno de los targets de la Tour guide.
  • Emergency teleport: Trae a uno de los Psychic gratis.
Inicio del combo:
  1. Primero, se debe traer a Cherubini y activar su efecto. No importa si es negado, ya que lo importante es el costo de enviar al cementerio a Graff para invocar del Deck a Cir (Ojo, si Cherubini mantiene sus efectos negados, Cir se destruirá si tenemos otros monstruos, así que cuidado).
  2. Hacemos link summon con cherubini y Cir, con lo que se activará el efecto de este último y así invocaremos nuevamente a Cherubini. El monstruo link que invocaremos dependerá de la ruta que elijamos, la cual a su vez depende de cuántos extenders tengamos disponibles.
Ruta segura (Número de extenders iniciales requerido: 4+. Monstruo: Apollousa):
  1. Al tener 2 extenders extra además de los usados para invocar a Cherubini, usaremos un material link más para ir por Apollousa. Opcionalmente si hay más extenders, se le puede invocar con 4 materiales para tener las 4 negaciones, pero siempre dejando 1 para el siguiente paso. También es importante no poner demasiados cuerpos, ya que más tarde van a estorbar.
  2. Con el extender sobrante y el Cherubini revivido por el efecto de Cir, invocaremos por link a Codebreaker virus swordsman, colinkeado a Apollousa. Esto activará el efecto de invocar del Deck a Codebreaker zero day.
  3. Usamos los codebreaker para invocar a Isolde. Añadimos cualquier descarte e invocamos a Armageddon knight. Para los equipos a descartar, es importante enviar Phoenix blade (combo guerrero), Sword of sparkles (ya verán) y Cursed bamboo sword (para añadirnos una magia a la mano).
  4. Armageddon enviará a Plaguespreader zombie, el cual reviviremos con el descarte de Isolde, luego usaremos estos dos para invocar a Halqifibrax.
  5. Halqifibrax traerá a Vylon cube, y él junto con Armageddon invocarán por sincronía al Shooting riser dragon. Es importante NO ponerlo debajo de las flechas de Apollousa. Esto activará los efectos de Vylon cube (para traer un D.D.R.) y del Riser dragon (enviar al cementerio al World legacy - world chalice).
  6. Activamos el efecto del Phoenix blade para desterrar a Armageddon knight y otro guerrero cualquiera para añadirlo a la mano y lo descartamos como el coste del D.D.R. para invocar al mismo Armageddon desterrado.
  7. Con el efecto de Armageddon enviamos a Zephyr al cementerio. Activamos su efecto devolviendo a la mano el D.D.R. Armageddon irá al cementerio. Repetimos el paso 6.
  8. Esta vez enviaremos al cementerio al Summoner monk. Usaremos entonces a Zephyr y Armageddon para invocar a Dugares y revivir al Summoner Monk a la otra zona donde NO apunta Apollousa.
  9. Invocamos por Link al Flame swordsman usando a Dugares y Halqifibrax, y lo sacrificamos usando el efecto de Sword of sparkles. Con eso, todas las flechas debajo de Apollousa deberían estar libres. Usamos el efecto del Summoner monk descartando la Broken bamboo sword para invocar a Rescue ferret.
  10. Con Ferret traemos a Sangan, Lee y Spore (este último puede ser cualquier tuner de nivel 1). Dejando de lado a Lee, usamos los otros 2, además del Summoner monk y el Riser dragon (ahora de nivel 2) para hacer 2 invocaciones de sincronía: Ametrix (para invocar a Dewloren) y Rose maiden (para tener el Black garden).
  11. Con Sangan añadimos la primera pieza de Exodia: La pieza de efecto (por ser la más difícil de buscar)
  12. Activamos el Black garden y haremos una invocación link con Lee y Rose maiden, trayendo a Puzzlomino (su flecha debe estar libre)
  13. Activamos el efecto de Black garden para invocar al Summoner monk una vez más (no al lado de Puzzlomino)
  14. Activamos el efecto en el cementerio de la Rose maiden para traer al Riser dragon al lado de Puzzlomino y darle nivel 1 con el efecto de este último.
  15. Invocamos a Dewloren usando al Riser y Ametrix. Podemos traer el Phoenix blade a la mano una vez más para usarlo con el Summoner Monk por última vez para invocar al Treasure panda (es importante que esté en una zona a donde apunte Apollousa).
  16. Con el Treasure panda desterramos cualquier magia para invocar una pieza cualquiera de Exodia. Usamos esa pieza y a Puzzlomino para invocar a Lib y colocar el World legacy succession.
  17. Usamos a Lib y al Summoner monk para invocar a Tenyi y activamos el efecto de Lib para regresar al mismo Tenyi al Deck.
  18. Con eso, sólo debería quedar Dewloren y Treasure panda en la zona principal de monstruos. Usamos al panda para traer el resto de piezas de Exodia.
  19. Enviamos al Treasure panda al cementerio con el efecto de Lee y usamos el Succession para traer la pieza que enviamos al cementerio.
  20. Finalmente, devolvemos todas las piezas de Exodia a la mano con el efecto de Dewloren y GG.
Ruta parcialmente segura (Número de extenders iniciales requerido: 3. Monstruo: Tenyi)
  1. A diferencia de la primera ruta, sólo tenemos un extender adicional que debemos guardar para el codebreaker, así que usaremos solamente a Cherubini y Cir para invocar a Tenyi.
  2. El resto va igual hasta llegar al paso 9 de la ruta segura. En este punto, en lugar de invocar al Flame Swordsman con Halqifibrax y Dugares, usaremos ambos junto con el Tenyi para invocar a Apollousa.
  3. El combo continúa igual hasta el final. En la parte que se invoca a Tenyi usando a Lib y a Summoner monk, en su lugar invocaremos al Flame Swordsman (ya que Tenyi ya fue usado).
Ruta no segura (Número de extenders iniciales requerido: 2. Monstruo: Rusty bardiche)
  1. Esta ruta debería usarse como último recurso, en caso de tener una muy mala mano o que nos hayan destruido extenders. La ventaja es que no necesitamos a Cir, por lo que podemos ir directamente por el Edge imp sabres (para devolver un garnet al Deck, o a Brigandine si lo tenemos en la mano) con Cherubini, e ir por Rusty bardiche.
  2. Usaremos a Bardiche para enviar al cementerio a Cloak y colocar a Brigandine. Removemos a Cloak y robamos a Boots.
  3. Invocamos a Boots y Brigandine, yendo directamente a por Isolde (obviaremos a los codebreaker en esta ruta).
  4. El combo continúa igual que en la ruta segura, hasta llegar al paso 9.
  5. Ya que Bardiche no puede ser usado para invocaciones link, lo sacrificaremos con el Sword of Sparkles y usaremos a Dugares y Halqifibrax para invocar a Tenyi.
  6. Seguimos igual hasta el paso 17 (Phoenix blade puede volver a la mano sin problemas, ya que reemplazamos a los codebreaker por los phantom knights en esta ruta, que también son guerreros).
  7. Usamos entonces a Lib, Summoner monk y Tenyi para invocar a Apollousa, tras lo cual sigue todo igual hasta el final.
Tips:
  • Apollousa es útil para sacar del juego casi cualquier handtrap, aprovechando que Impermanence ya no se usa mucho y que Called está a 1 copia (por ahora 7w7)
  • Edge imp sabres y Plaguespreader zombie pueden usarse para enviar garnets en tu mano de vuelta al Deck. Algunos garnets que debes devolver serían los targets de Rescue Ferret o Armageddon Knight y alguna carta de equipo (en caso de robar 3 con nombres distintos y que no sean D.D.R.)
  • Si tienes el Sword of sparkles, puedes descartarlo en el primer uso del Summoner monk, o si tienes el Phoenix blade, equípaselo al Armageddon knight cuando lo invocas por primera vez para que vaya al cementerio.
  • Si tienes al Armageddon knight en tu mano, puedes invocar en su lugar al Dark grepher y usar su efecto para descartar al Armageddon knight, a la vez que envías al Plaguespreader zombie al cemenerio.
  • Si robas a Sangan, puedes usarlo como normal summon, añadir a Exodia cuando se vaya al cementerio, y más adelante reemplazarlo por cualquier otro monstruo de nivel 3.
  • Si robas el Black garden, puedes usarlo como coste del Summoner monk, ya que el efecto de Rose maiden lo añadirá del cementerio a tu mano más adelante.
  • No es posible realizar el combo con sólo 1 extender, pero las posibilidades de que sólo saques 1 o ninguno son cerca del 1% (sí, saqué las cuentas)
Pros:
  • Deck extremadamente consistente, sólo brickea alrededor del 1% de las veces.
  • Versátil. Se adapta fácilmente a los recursos que tengamos en mano.
  • Protegido constantemente por Apollousa, por lo que es difícil de contrarrestarlo una vez toca el campo.
  • No depende del burn, por lo que no le afectan cartas como Ghost sister u otras que le permitan ganar LP al oponente.
  • No requiere demasiados recursos para realizar el combo. Con 2 extenders es suficiente, y tener más solamente lo hace mejor.
  • Puede baitear hantraps tempranas con los extenders suficientes.
Contras:
  • A pesar de ser consistente, tiene muchos garnets, por lo que es posible comenzar con 3+ garnets en mano, en cuyo caso es un gg automático.
  • Debe ser efectuado al detalle. Si se falla en un pequeño detalle, muy probablemente el campo se llene de monstruos inútiles. Una parte importante del Deck es por eso, deshacerse de lo que estorba con Sword of Sparkles, Lib y Lee. Además, las posiciones donde se invoca algunos monstruos son muy importantes.
  • Aún teniendo protección, el Deck es susceptible a Nibiru, Impermanence y Called by the grave si son usados correctamente.
  • Si destruyen a Cherubini antes de activar su efecto y no hay forma de invocarlo del cementerio, también es gg.

deck_excerpt: It aims to enable the infinite summoning of monsters /// Visa possibilitar a invocação infinita de monstros.
deck_description: The strategy consists of invoking the Six Samurai Link, seeking the Gateway of the Six from the deck, in addition to using the Dojo or Field Spell. In this way, each time a Six Samurai is invoked, 4 counters will be generated, the same amount required to search for a Six Samurai from GY/Deck. Add the Six Samurai that summon yourself from the hand, so you can summon as many monsters as you want. In addition, it should be noted that a trap card has been included in the deck, which limits the number of summons to 2. The trap card can be found with the XYZ Primathmech Alembertian. ________________________________________________________________________________________ A estratégia consiste em invocar o Six Samurai Link, buscando a Gateway of the Six do baralho, além de utilizar a Dojo ou a Field Spell. Desta forma, cada vez que um Six Samurai for invocado, serão gerados 4 contadores, a mesma quantidade requerida para buscar um Six Samurai do GY/Deck. deck_description: Category: Tournament Meta Deck  Tournament Meta Decks are current level Meta Decks that are capable of going up against the best of the best. Creator: Cesar Rodriguez Tournament: NA Remote Duel Invitational – February 14 to February 15th 2021 Placement: 1st Place  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Q4mRsWApUe0

Pretty basic Phantom Knights core with a tiny Malebranche of the BA engine, to get a Cherubini on field and targets for RUMF in the graveyard. Pretty standard stuff, but Raider's Wing going second and Revolution Falcon give this deck the oomf it sometimes lacks. Monsters: The first line of cards are your extenders, you want to see at least one in your opening hand (Torn Scales obviously the best). Cloak is the first card to get in your GY, and Boots is usually your last and usually not a target for Rusty or Torn Scales. Gloves is a decent extender off of Rusty's effect. Kagemucha Knight, Psychics and E-Tele (even Boots) are going to be your special summon after your starter. The six hand traps are flexible. Spells/Traps: E-Tele gets an extender or during your opponent's turn is a free disruption (using Ghost Ogre). RUMF goes into Revolution Falcon. PK Wing is an extender. Fog Blade puts in work and ROTA and Foolish start plays. Extra Deck: Cherubini and Rusty are cards you want to go into every time, and then Leviair if you have the resources. Break Sword goes into Dark Rebellion or Nightmare. Use your Cherubini bringing it back with Cir to go into Verte most of the time and then Dragoon. Falcon for RUMF and free pop. Accesscode Talker is your main means of OTK. Masquerena package for extra negates or to spin cards if you can't get an ideal board. Link Spider is pretty nice as it can link for Shade Brigadine to get an effect monster on field for further Extra Deck stuff and also to save you if you get Nibiru'd. My favourite combo (ideal hand) off this deck goes Normal Torn Scales, discarding Cloak and sending Raider's Wing. Get extender on field (any Lv 3) and link into Cherubini, send Graff and Special Cir (Libic, if you drew Cir) and link away Cherubini and Cir for ya boi Rusty, sending Gloves and setting a Fog Blade. Banish Cloak adding Boots and use Torn effect to Special him. Special Boots and overlay into Levinair, detaching to special Cloak in attack, activate and target Rusty. Activate Gloves, sending PK Wing and banish Wing to Special Boots again. Overlay Boots and Cloak into Break Sword to a Rusty zone, use either his own (activate Raider's Wing first) or Rusty's effect to self-destroy and activate, bringing back any two of you PKs. Overlay them into a. Nightmare to basically deny your opponent next turn or b. Dark Rebellion to punch in for damage. Your Nightmare is basically broooooken if you use your Raider's Wing. Link away your Leviair and Cherubini to Anaconda and the next is obvious. Main 2 you banish Boots to set RUMF (one Fog Blade is usually enough, using it more than once a turn causes trouble next turn). You cause a Nightmare for your opponent their turn and once it's out of gas, you activate RUMF, banishing your Malebranche's and go into Revolution Falcon, popping your opponents only face-up or any monster. Accesscode for game, almost 80% of the time. You can take out the Masquerena package for the Raider's Knight to Arc Rebellion Combo and also add Almiraj in for added consistency in getting out Dragoon. Almiraj is probably the best change if you're looking to make the deck a lil' more consistent. All in all, an insanely fun deck.

deck_excerpt: An unconventionnal yet very fun deck that tries to break boards before winning through attrition or OTK. Make the best use of Abhyss archetype, Snake
deck_description: First of all, you NEVER want to go first. Your endboard will most likely suck. This deck has way more power going second. You might have seen versions with viruses and other weird lair-related stuff, it makes the deck inconsistent while having an okay-ish endboard. Sure, going first IF you can assemble all 3 of the Abhyss boss monsters, you have a decent board, but nothing crazy and you need to open some disgustingly good hand to assemble it (which this deck could as well). The payoff for going first is really low, but you can consider siding some viruses if you know your opponents is going to make you go first.  The idea is to injure the opponents board with strong equalizers before spamming your field with reptiles and accessing your Xyz 8 toolbox. Curse and Aleth make it easy with snake rain so you can end game quickly with Numeron Dragon. If you can't otk that turn, then setup your Aron and Amunesia to disrupt your opponent's follow up.  Lair of darkness is insane in this deck and so is Darkest Diabolos. You can tribute your opponent's monster to summon yours from the graveyard , which bypasses almost every kind of protection. It's one of the easier ways to get rid of problematic cards. Even Arima is nice, not only because it searches Lair, but it's effect is actually useful : you can search Nihil, Nessie, Jackalope or Diabolos depending on what you need.  Lamia, Echidna and Hydra are nice little engine that clears boards and gives you cards to work with. It doesn't interact well with targeting protection though. Be careful with Echidna, as her search effect prevents you from going into your Rank 8.  Dangers are here for "consistency" and they open up Xyz play. Its weird to speak about consistency with danger!s but that's what they actually do here, kind of how they did in Thunder dragon back in the days. There is just no better equivalent to "extenders that load the graveyard and cycle through the deck" and you need all of that. Tsuchinoko is searchable with King of the Feral Imp or Echidna, which is actually very relevant because one more monster can be crucial to tribute for your Abhyss graveyard summons.  If you don't open your equalizers, try baiting as much negates as you can, you will see that you can go through much.  The side deck is just good going second cards, but you can put whatever you like as long as you can break boards. Careful with the barrier statue of the wind, as you will need the wind insect kaiju to out it as Gameciel don't work. Be sure to pack Backrow hate as that kind of deck can become akward to deal with. As I said before, viruses can also be considered in the side for going first.  Weakness to droll&lockbird,  Skullmeister, Ghost Belle and backrow heavy decks.  Some edit after more playtest : added Number 23 Lancelot and AA-Zeus, super good if you can't otk.  Let me know in the comments if you would make any changes or if you disagree with my point of view. Hell you can comment if you like the deck as well ! I truly believe this is the good route ! Enjoy !

Another variant of Tri-brigade. If "bird up!" (lyrilusc Tri-brigade) is considered competitive, then I don't know how the heck this one isn't. But people never cared about Simorgh cards...  The litte simorgh chickens act as your normal summons AND free extenders (if your opponent' BR is empty, which is always the case going first) to go into Chicken of Sovereignty. Bringing searches a simorgh card on normal summon, and Calamity foolishes one. Calamity is actually a one-card Chicken of sovereignty if your hand is poor.  Bringing can search multiple cards depending on what you need :  -if you open Both him and Calamity, or Elborz : search the other piece, activate the field spell and foolish the chicken of protection on calamity norm and bang! you have the setup for the infamous "infinite negate combo" without even going into your tri-brigades yet. If you open Bringing, elborz and something to discard, search Onslaught instead.  -if you open him and nerval : search the field spell, normal nerval and go into linkuriboh so you can search Kerass and do your Tri-brigade plays.  -if you open him and fractaur ( and no other mentionned pieces ) : search sky battle for extra protection.  -you can side-in the big chicken Simorgh of Ancestry going second, for example against Vanity ruler or Winda. Then you need to open Bringing and Elborz, Ancestry or Onslaught : you can use both effect of elborz to tribute summon the big chicken to out up to 2 cards, without targeting, destroying or even special summoning.     Onslaught is very good as it searches 2 cards and loads your graveyard. The two big dark chickens are enablers for it but you card also end on Dark simorgh if you're going against a backrow heavy deck. The other one can be summoned during the Bird of ancestry shenanigan.  Now for the BIG DEAL : Harpie's feather storm. This card is NOT OKAY. Effectivly Azathot in a trap card, unfair by nature. It is sooooo good that trap trick made it's way into the main deck. Even if your whole turn was negated by handtraps or if you get Dark ruler no mored or Forbidden Droppleted, as long as you have a wind winged beast one the field and HFS set, your opponents will most likely end his turn as he won't be able to play Yugioh. Even "normal summon barrier statue, set HFS" is a sick turn. Pair it with Sovereignty and you have a really oppressive board. That is why that's is a mandatory 6 of. You will most likely side out your traps going second but HFS can be use as a dark ruler no more like effect when harpie conductor is on the field, in very niche scenarios.  Be careful to summon your tri-brigades before summoning back your simorgh chickens, as they lock your into winged-beast when summoned this way.     Compared to "bird up!", this deck can't go into Zeus but compensates by having an easier access to one of the most unfair trap cards ever, the deadly "infinite negate combo" with union carrier and mist valley thunderbird and much more value from normal summons. Aside from this, things are pretty similar. You also get to use The bird of sovereignty's protection effect.  Let me know in the comments if you would change anything ! Enjoy chickens !

deck_excerpt: @Ignister deck w/ Lightning Vortex support  (Also, a reference to Yu-Gi-Oh! Japanese dub)
deck_description: Wow, I am one lazy mother****er. Anyways...this here is my new @Ignister deck, using their new support cards from Lightning Vortex.  Keeping with the pun theme of the deck's backrow, this deck is named "A.I.bou", after the Japanese word for "partner"(Aibou). What makes this even more appropriate is that Ai was Yusaku's partner in Yu-Gi-Oh VRAINS, and some of Yusaku's cards work excellently in @Ignister decks. Also, Yami Yugi calls Yugi Muto this a lot in Yu-Gi-Oh!'s Japanese dub.     Dark Infant @Ignister gives a massive boost to this deck's consistency, because it can search @Ignister A.I.land upon summon, can move to a Main Monster Zone it points to, and change its attribute. This makes summoning The Arrival Cyberse @Ignister easier, and Dark Infant's search effect means you don't need to run Terraforming or 3 copies of A.I.land.  When A.I. first met you is the best Normal Spell in the deck, because it can search an @Ignister monster, and your only cost is that you must reveal a Cyberse monster in your hand or Extra Deck that has 2300 ATK. And @Ignister has those Extra Deck monsters in spades! So 3 of this and 3 Cynet Mining gives @Ignister S-class consistency!     As for this deck's strategy, it works fine going first or second. If you're going first, your goal is to summon The Arrival Cyberse @Ignister, preferably with Danmari @Ignister in your Graveyard so you can negate one of your opponent's cards. If you're going second, your goal is to go on the offensive with your Extra Deck monsters. You can OTK your opponent with Dark Templar, Wind Pegasus, and Light Dragon. Or you can summon Accesscode Talker with Update Jammer, leaving you with a 4300 to 5300-ATK board wipe that can attack twice.

deck_excerpt: A simple execution for the twins
deck_description: Destruction & havoc upon our little twins!

This version of the deck now ensures that you won't be ending up passing on 1 monster for the most part going first. That said, you need to draw Xyz Change Tactics or the deck literally won't function and you would rather choose to go second. At best, you can pass your turn with Artifact Durendal/Constellar Peliades, Dragonic Utopia Ray with 3 or more ZW cards attached to it including a ZW - Dragonic Halberd, and 1 other Utopia monster which you can choose to equip with ZW cards as well. ZS - Ascend Sage and ZS - Arms Sage are the heart and soul of this deck. They are your only play starters and they provide the most consistent searching in the entire deck since ZEXAL Construction is still a neg 1. Another important playmaker in this deck is Summoner Monk as it functions as a play starter and extender. You rarely normal summon in this deck and Monk can get you material for another xyz summon. ZW - Pegasus Twin Saber and Eagle Claw may provide things like monster and trap negates, but they are here since they bolster your board with Rank 5 access. Lightning Blade is the most important card in the deck when you are going through with summoning Durendal since it protects your ZW equips from being destroyed and hardly anyone reads cards. Tornado Bringer is just another name and it provides targeting protection. Asura Arms makes your Utopia into a UCT (or an actual one if you decide to play Phoenix Bow). You need to see your combo pieces in this deck and things like ROTA, Desires, Generation Shift, and Xyz Change Tactics all get you there. You need to see Xyz Change Tactics or else you will actually be passing on 1 monster turn 1. ZEXAL Entrust provides much needed recycling and extending for the deck. RUM ZEXAL Force easily searchable in this deck and it stacks a ZW or ZS so that you draw what you need with Tactics. ZEXAL Construction is a neg 1, but you need to play it since it searches like half the deck. Also 1 Double or Nothing! to make use of Utopia Double. Extra Deck: Zeus is a staple in xyz decks. Gaia Drake just gives Zeus more material. Constellar Pleiades & Artifact Durendal are your Rank 5 targets, but you can choose to play something like Volcasaurus over Pleiades since you usually won't have 2 lights since Eagle Claw is a wind. 1 Dragonic Utopia Ray to OTK. 1 Leo Utopia Ray since its a negate and it equips from ED also. 1 ZW - Dragonic Halberd for more OTK potential. You can also choose to play his brother,  ZW - Leo Arms, if you want another Rank 5 target. 1 Utopia the Lightning. 1 Utopia Ray V. 1 Utopia Ray. 1 Utopia Prime (don't sleep on this one). 1 Utopia Double. And 3 Number 39: Utopia. All you need to know about the side deck is that V Salamander gets you back advantage later in the game, Xyz Encore counters xyz decks and it is searchable off of Generation Force, Shining Draw is like an okay card, and ZEXAL Alliance is another way to gain back advantage despite making you vulnerable to Sparks.

Welcome to the Zombie World!  Suggestions are welcome.     Pros:  Consistent ending board on Halqifibrax, Vampire Sucker, I:P/ Verte Anaconda, Dragoon, and Balerdroch (+2 Draw, ~4 disruptions)  ~64% chance to draw a 1 card combo to Halq Turn 1  ~95% chance to draw a 2 card combo to Halq  Turn 1  ~64% chance to draw Zombie World Turn 1  ~57% chance to draw a 'Monster Reborn'  Built-in floodgate with Zombie World  Few flexible spots in the extra deck to allow for adaptation for different metas: Knightmare Phoenix, Unicorn, Halquifibrax and Dagda can be replaced with Dugaress, Abyss Dweller, Daigusto Emeral, Accesscode Talker, ETC.  Ability to switch to different styles depending on side deck  The deck has a lot of extenders, allowing for options in play depending on the situation.  Cons:  Prone to Handtraps.  Poor recovery after disruptions; you will possibly use the whole hand to reach the primary board and +2 draw on the opponents turn with Formula Synchron and Vampire Sucker  Typically will need to use all in-hand extenders to reach the end board.  Difficult to break established boards without siding.
Reclaim the Amazon from the civilised by dominating the battle phase through exclusively somewhat frustrating means.

Attempt to defeat your opponent through the power of nostalgia but actually win primarily with Rampage OTK and Infinity Control. The duels where you get to BM by winning with Twin or End are what you strive for.

deck_excerpt: A quick idea build: Tenyi w/ Invoked
deck_description:
As the title implies, this is a TEMPLATE and by no means is this a finished deck. The idea is here, and you can do what you want with this. This is not even close to the full potential this deck could obtain. I know this isn't the best deck to come back with after months of inactivity, but it's the most original idea I have at the moment. Okay, with that disclaimer out of the way, here's the premiss. I've been a longtime fan of Tenyi builds. They can play around Nibiru, Gamma and Impermanence with relative ease and don't use up your Normal Summon. For this reason, things like Lava Golem, Invoked and other normal-summon heavy engines work quite well with it. The Tenyi normal deck monsters are also all different Attributes, lending itself pretty well to both Shaddoll and Invoked fusion monsters. So, I thought, why not? Lets make a Tenyi Invoked deck. Some things right off the bat: you almost always want to used your invoked engine AFTER your done with Tenyis. That way, you can use whatever Tenyi's you want in your fusion summons. There's also a neat little combo you can pull off with the Tenyi search spell, any Tenyi monster and a way to get Aleister (I'll detail that later). You won't be normal summoning Aleister until late into your turn, after all your Tenyi plays. Even when Nibiru is played, you should be able to end on a Sahasrara and/or an Invoked monster, if you get either Aleister or the field spell. A few problems with the deck as it is: there are hardly any negates (you typically won't be getting SAVAGE first turn, if ever, and Mechaba is only 1), feeble draw power (someone will figure out that one, also I'm lazy and didn't imput Desires, so that is a viable option. Prosperity is only useful because you can choose what to banish, but generally your Extra Deck is necessary), lack of removal, and a lack of viable floodgate bypasses (pretty much anything will kill it). The power of the deck is underwhelming as it is, but this can be ammended in future installations. Let me know what you think! Here's the combo for you:
  1. Special Summon whatever Tenyi you have
  2. Link to Monk
  3. Activate Vessel for the Dragon Cycle, mill Mare Mare, add Ashuna or Adhara or Mapura (depending on what Invoked you want)
  4. Special Summon the Tenyi you have
  5. Link to Shaman
  6. Special Summon Mare Mare from grave using Shaman. Use Mare Mare to get 2 (or 3) tokens.
  7. Link Shaman and 2 (or 3) tokens to Ashuna
  8. Use Mare to get another token to make him Lvl. 4 if you haven't already
  9. Normal Summon Aleister, adding Invocation (if necessary, get the field spell to search him out)
  10. Synchro Summon Draco Berserker using Mare Mare and Aleister (SAVAGE won't activate because of Shaman)
  11. Use Invocation to bring out appropriate Invoked (you usually want to go for Mechaba, since it's a negate).

Sky scourge is a fairly unique archetype, it plays really weird though and needs light fairy and dark fiends to function. Turns out the best way to do that is, well, monarchs apparently. Domain Monarchs in this case because they are the best form of monarchs.

3 sky scourge sidherz (new support card for lighting overdrive, both foolish and reinforcement of the army for dark fiends and light fairies, really good card)

3 sky scourge norleras (full hand rip, now that’s savage)

2 sky scourge enrise (removal by banishment)

2 sky scourge invicel (spell and trap stopper, might put at one in the future)

3 edios the underworld squire (fun squire to have, recycles the other squire and is a dark fiend)

3 edea the heavenly squire (squire/vassal searcher, good to have and a can’t do without, plus it’s light fairy)

1 mithra the thunder vassal (ez body on field in return for your opponent to get a monster that’ll get domain locked anyways)

3 Erebus the underworld monarch (the face of domain monarchs, recycler, hand rip, and foolish)

3 ehther the heavenly monarch (summon monarch from deck dude)

1 Kurtz the light monarch (monarch’s version of Maximus but better in some ways, worse in other ways)

1 Lucifer the shadow vassal (know what’s set plus easy summon)

1 vanity’s fiend (haha, you can’t summon)

1 majesty’s fiend (haha, no monster effects)

3 domain of the monarchs (the main card, extra deck lock, now imagine that but with norleras performing a full hand rip, yes, I can feel your fear already)

3 phantasm of the monarchs (An anti brick, pluses one (discard draw 2 then searches spell))

3 tendency of the monarchs (a search, because that’s just helpful)

3 the monarchs stormforth (Tribute opponents monsters? Sign me up!)

1 one for one (ez heavenly squire = ez monarch)

1 foolish burial (multi purpose card)

2 the prime monarch (“yo dude, I saw your graveyard was getting filled up so I unclogged it for you”)

The main idea is using the monarchs in order to fill your grave and then use the sky scourges summonings to start brutalizing the field with the removal that monarchs lack, I’ve yet to test this deck but I imagine it’ll be fun (for you, not for them), provided you don’t brick.

The new sky scourge is super good. I found that he can be used for a lot of situations.

Strengths and weaknesses:

Strong points:

  1. ABSOLUTELY MURDERS certain decks, pretty much anything that needs an extra deck will just have to be prepared to die (Salamangreat, HEROS, numeron, bird up, invoked, heck there’s even a rare chance of this beating VW if you go first)
  2. You have lots of removal, lockdown, and things to destroy your opponents resources
  3. We have something pretty similar to dogmokita maximus, but our version may be better (first we get pick what to rip out of extra deck, then we can destroy opponents field, sadly they get to draw for this but in all cases we still use norleras if you’re lucky enough to get him out on the same turn you do this)
  4. Occasional full hand rip via norleras
  5. Decently Nibiruproof
  6. Dogmokita can’t do much to you, and you can still hand rip them!

Weak points:

  1. Eldlich don’t care
  2. Main play is a floodgate that can get destroyed pretty quickly
  3. Card advantage isn’t going to be coming easily for you
  4. Dies to certificate handtraps
  5. Droll and lock kills you
  6. Uses lots of resources to do things
  7. Spell/traps for monarchs, though good, are way too gimmicky for their own good
  8. Drytron kills this deck
  9. Know those monarch brick memes? Yeah, here’s the brickiest variant yet

The main move of this deck is similar to other domain decks, it is to tribute summon a monster on your first turn then dump domain of the monarchs out on your field. This is easily achieved by edea the heavenly squire who will summon edios the underworld squire, edios gives you another tribute summon the turn he comes out on the field. You got a lot of good options for this but my favorite so far is ehther the heavenly monarch, ehther can summon kurtz who’ll preform an extra deck rip.

Another cool note is that norleras, though hard to summon at times, preforms a full hand rip for the small price of 1000 life points, that sort of effect can end duels before they even started, it is also an effect that had cards get banned.

The dream field to get is sky scourge norleras, tribute summoned monster, and monarch’s domain.

deck_excerpt: Competitive Hero deck utilizing Elemental, Masked, Destiny and Xtra Heroes to get fun OTKS
deck_description:
Combos   Elemental HERO Solid Soldier+Vision HERO Vyon
  1. Normal summon Solid Soldier which special summons Vyon
  2. Vyon sends Destiny HERO Malicious to GY
  3. Banish Malicious from GY to special summon another Malicious
  4. Link Solid Soldier+Malicious into Xtra HERO Cross Crusader
  5. Cross Crusader special summons Malicious back
  6. Use Cross Crusader to tribute Malicious which adds Elemental HERO Honest Neos to hand
  7. Activate Vyon to banish Solid Soldier to find Polymerization and add it to hand
  8. Link Vyon+Cross Crusader into Xtra HERO Infernal Devicer
  9. Infernal Devicer reveals Flame Wingman adding Avian and Burstinatrix to hand
  10. Polymerization Avian+Burstinatrix into Elemental HERO Sunrise
  11. Sunrise will add Miracle Fusion to hand
  12. Miracle Fusion into Flame Wingman/Sunrise/Grandmerge
  13. Use Honest Neos on Grandmerge to destroy a monster to tribute Grandmerge and summon Flame Wingman/Absolute Zero
  1. Flame Wingman destroys another monster and deals damage
End Board: Infernal Devicer, Sunrise, Flame Wingman/Absolute Zero, Honest Neos (In hand)   Elemental HERO Stratos+Elemental HERO Solid Soldier+Vision HERO Faris/Malicious/Shadow Mist
  1. Normal summon Solid Soldier to special summon Stratos
  2. Stratos finds either Faris, or if Faris is already in hand then finds Shadow Mist
  3. Pitch Shadow Mist to special summon Faris
  4. Faris places Increase into zone
  5. Tribute Faris to special summon Increase
  6. Increase special summons Vyon
  7. Vyon sends Malicious to GY
  8. Banish Malicious to special summon another Malicious
  9. Link Increase+Malicious into Cross Crusader
  10. Cross Crusader special summons Malicious from GY
  11. Cross Crusader tributes Malicious to find Liquid Soldier
  12. Vyon banishes Faris from GY to find polymerization to hand
  13. Polymerization Liquid Soldier+Solid Soldier into Sunrise
  14. Solid Soldier special summons Shadow Mist from GY
  15. Shadow Mist finds Mask Change
  16. Sunrise finds Miracle Fusion
  17. Liquid Soldier draws 2 cards then discards 1
  18. Link Stratos+Cross Crusader into Wonder Driver
  19. Mask Change Vyon into Dark Law
  20. Wonder Driver sets Mask Change
  21. Miracle Fusion Liquid Soldier+other HERO (Solid Soldier) into Absolute Zero
End Board: Wonder Driver, Sunrise, Dark Law, Absolute Zero, Shadow Mist, Mask Change

deck_excerpt: Ruin your opponent's day with Springan's Ship (with some scrappy bois)
deck_description: Springans Ship can really ruin your opponent's day, and it's not too hard to pull off. If you have Great Sand Sea and a Springans monster (or Springans Watch to search either) in your hand, you're set! Use Great Sand Sea to XYZ summon Ship, attach the Springans as material per their effect, detach them to target a zone, and boom! Board broken. The Scrap engine helps with consistency. Using it to send Springans to the graveyard is helpful because they can attach to Ship from the GY. It's also useful to spam out effect monsters as Anaconda mats for the Dragoon engine, if you choose to main that. Zeus works with mostly every XYZ strategy, and adds another board wipe.

deck_description: The Yu-Gi-Oh! Trading Card Game Known as the Yu-Gi-Oh! Official Card Game (遊☆戯☆王オフィシャルカードゲーム, Yū-Gi-Ō Ofisharu Kādo Gēmu) in Asia, is a Japanese collectible card game developed and published by Konami. It is based on the fictional game of Duel Monsters created by manga artist Kazuki Takahashi, which is the main plot device during the majority of the manga franchise, Yu-Gi-Oh, and its various anime adaptations and spinoff series. "Endymion" (エンディミオン Endimion) is an archetype that debuted in Structure Deck: Lord of the Magician, with further support in Structure Deck R: Lord of Magician. "Endymion, the Master Magician" appears as a character in Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's World Championship 2009: Stardust Accelerator and has a Duel School related to it in Yu-Gi-Oh! ARC-V, and "Crusader of Endymion" appears in Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's World Championship 2010: Reverse of Arcadia". deck_name: The Banished Emperor - Gren Maju OTK
deck_excerpt: Tried of boring combos and brain numbing dueling? Are you a Yugi-Boomer (like me) who just want simple unga bunga smackdown caveman Yu-Gi-Oh? This dec
deck_description: Tried of boring combos and brain numbing dueling? Are you a Yugi-Boomer (like me) who just want simple unga bunga smackdown caveman Yu-Gi-Oh? Excited to break your opponent's board that they so lovingly crafted the last 10 minutes with their ridiculously long cardplay (zzzZZZzzz)? Wanna obliterate your opponent with an oldschool 15 year old card in one single attack? Gren Maju OTK is the perfect deck for you!   Popularized by the venerable Yishan McNabb nearly two years ago by gaining second place in YCS August 2019 during the infamous control heavy "TOSS" format, this Gren Maju OTK made a surprising splash as a rogue meta contender ever since.   This deck focuses on the straight forward strategy banishment into one shot kill with a ridiculously OMEGA-POWERFUL high attack Gren Maju De Eiza, who gains 400 attack from everyone of your banished cards. This deck is best-tailored with cards and engines best enable this simple strategy.   This deck features 3 packages that feature level 8 monsters that pair nicely with Trade-In (Discard lvl8 for +2 draw) and allows rank 8 plays.   Danger! Package are composed of absolute chonkers that special summon themselves from the hand and a +1 draw if special summoned successfully with their effect - given if you're lucky. If they get discarded with their own effect, they destroy a card on the field. Danger! Bigfoot destroys face-up cards, while Danger! Thunderbird destroys face-downs. They have incredible synergy with Trade-In, not only you get a +2 draw when you discard a Danger! monster, you get to destroy a card on the field! Golden Castle Package features the field spell Golden Castle of Stromberg, which simultaneously destroys attacking monsters for burn damage and special summons from the deck Hexe Trude (level 8 with 1 destruction per turn) and Glife the Phantom Bird (Golden Castle searcher and backrow destruction). Golden Castle also banishes 10 cards from your maindeck everyturn, additionally boosting Gren Maju's attack! Funnily with Golden Castle on the field, opponents usually never read the additional card text on it and still foolishly attack with their monsters - blowing up their monster for delicious burn damage! Kaiju Package are one of your ultimate board breaking tools! Tribute away their invincible towers (I'm looking at you Dragoon >:c) or their annoying quick effect monster (I hate you Altergeist Silquitous)! Our monsters of choice are the level 8 Gameciel (chosen for its relatively low 2200 attack, making OTKs slightly easier) and Gadarla. Interrupted Kaiju Slumber clears an entire field of monsters as long as there is a copy of Gameciel and Gadarla in the still in the deck. Try to use this before you banish your main deck so you don't accidentally banish your kaijus!   Field Equalizers   As a dedicated going second deck, deck features field equalizers that obliterate your opponent's field to wipe away all opposition, so that Gren Maju De Eiza can annihilate! Lightning Storm is The most expensive card in the deck (About $100 each as of this writing) and it is incredibly powerful. It can wipe either backrow or attack position monsters given the player using it doesn't have face-up cards. This is useful going second and the gren maju player will have plenty of opportunity to use this card because their field will mostly be empty. This card can be replaced by a cheaper alternative like Twin Twisters or Dark Hole (still not quite the same or as powerful unfortunately, hope this card gets reprinted soon). Raigeki is a great card and requires no explanation, smash your opponent's monsters! Interrupted Kaiju Slumber clears an entire field of monsters as long as there is a copy of Gameciel and Gadarla in the still in the deck. Try to use this before you banish your main deck so you don't accidentally banish your kaijus! Dinowrestler Pankratops is the only non-spell card featured in the board breaking line-up. It is a dedicated going-second card that puts a free body on board, and it can tribute itself to destroy any card on the field. For backrow heavy decks, exchange cards in your deck like Twin Twisters or Harpie's Feather Duster. (For example, you won't need kaijus as much vs. Mystic Mine, so replace the entire kaiju package with backrow hate like this.) Other cards like Gizmek Orochi and Hexe Trude provide singular card destruction as well to assist with board breaking. If something is particularly difficult to get rid of, Dingirsu can send a card from the field to the GY.   Banishment Enablers   Gren Maju feeds on the souls of the banished to boost his attack by 400 for every banished card! We have several cards that banish en masse in this deck to serve their Banished Emperor, Gren Maju. Pot of Desires is almost a free +2 draw for Gren Maju players, boosting his attack by 4000 everytime this card is used. Careful about banishing important parts of your packages, it may render some cards like Golden Castle of Stromberg or Interrupted Kaiju Slumber un-useable. Eater of Millions in addition to having a badass name, it also is a force to be reckoned with for every monster it battles. Its attack features non-targeting banishment, serving as a out to meta threats like Dragoon! It has unusual protection too, and it cannot be used as material for fusion so it cannot be removed with Super Poly! It can get pretty big, gaining+100 attack for every facedown banished card so it can hit over big targets. A favourite play of mine is banishing my entire extra deck, netting +6000 attack for Gren Maju! Gizmek Orochi, the Serpentron Sky Slasher functions as an excellent banishment tool because it banishes cards as a cost for it's effects, further boosting Gren Maju De Eiza's attack. It can also serve as a body shield when you're in a pinch, because it can summon itself from the graveyard as a quick effect. Orochi assists with rank 8 plays. If this card is XYZ material for a rank 8, detach it first so it can resurrect itself for the GY! To top it all off, Orochi can destroy a face-up monster on the field for the low cost 3 banished extra deck cards! Dimension Shifter is arguably the strongest and most underrated hand trap, shutting off graveyard access for both players by banishing every card sent to the graveyard until the end of next turn it is activated. Almost every deck is reliant on the GY nowadays, and Dimension Shifter effectively shuts them down. If you see this guy in your opening hand, the duel's momentum is yours for a while, giving you plenty of space and time to OTK with Gren Maju!   Extra Deck   The extra deck serves not only as fodder to summon Eater of Millions, it is full of toolbox options for your rank 8 plays, as well as link plays as you swarm the board with a ton of special summons. The terrific trio of the "Number Dragons" Number 97: Draglubion, Number 38: Hope Harbinger and Number 100: Numeron Dragon provide a lot of utility and usage of the multiple level 8 monsters in this deck. Draglubion also enables the easy summon of Hope Harbinger and Numeron Dragon. Hope Harbinger is terrific going first, as it allows for a spell negate. An even more powerful play going second is clearing the board then summoning Numeron Dragon off Draglubion and hitting for 9000ATK! If Gren Maju is inaccessible, Numeron Dragon is this deck's secondary way to OTK. Number 68: Sanaphond is also another going first option, shutting off GY summons until the end of the opponent's turn. Personally, I hardly ever make this card. It may serve to stifle the occasional deck that loves GY summons like Salamangreat or Zombies. Dingirsu, the Orcust of the Evening Star is simultaneously a great removal option and blanket protection from destruction. A good play I like to do with this guy is protecting Golden Castle of Stromberg by using Hexe Trude + another level 8 as material just to stall until I draw the perfect card. The link monsters Knightmare Unicorn/Phoenix provide target removal. The Topologic duo of Zeroboros and Trisbaena provide banishment removal, and is best triggered by summoning Gizmek Orochi during your opponent's turn. Black Luster Soldier - Soldier of Chaos is a great way to make use of the high level monsters on your field to provide his extra protection and is a great boss monster.   Link 1 monsters Linkuriboh and Relinquished Anima provide a way for level 1 Eater of Millions more utility. A great way to use Relinquished Anima is to suck up the kaiju you summoned to your opponent's field to further clear their field.   Side Deck   The side deck features cards that destroy the current meta. Change it according to how the meta changes. The best cards to switch out of this deck are the Kaiju and Golden Castle packages. Switch them out as needed verses particular decks. For example vs. combo (ex. Virtual World), you switch in Nibiru. Verses decks that love to banish (ex. dino) you switch in Artifact Lancea. Against decks that use heavy backrow (ex. Eldlich) trade in Twin Twisters and Harpie's Feather Duster. The Psy-Frame Gamma Package also provides a lot of utility with this deck as well, especially when you want to negate + destroy an important choke point (ex. Halqifibrax/Isolde).   Final Comments   This deck is definitely strong, but it does have it's weaknesses. It really has no strong going first play, and you can only hope that your opponent does not OTK you on the following turn. If you don't manage to OTK your opponent, this deck has little to no ability to grind out a game - once you run out of resources, you deck yourself out because you banished everything you own. This deck is super fun and easy to play. It has highly potent board breaking capabilities, it is very consistent, and high game-ending attack on board is easy to achieve. Games are finished quickly, it is relatively stress free, and it's pretty straightforward. I highly recommend bringing this if it is your first time in locals and you are worried you may misplay from nervousness or something. There is something super satisfying beating your opponent to a pulp with one singular attack with a super-powerful monster, which hearkens memories of simple caveman Yu-Gi-Oh from ancient times.   Good luck have fun duelists! o7
Musty Dusty StarDust
Lead Memory Boxer

A combo deck with time thiefs. The goal is to make the wise strik combo to end on a board of some negates plus redoer with a trap as material. Basic Combo :
  1. Summon TT regulator, use its effect to summon Winder and Bezel Ship (BS)
  2. Winder effect to grab Retrograde
  3. XYZ for Force Strix (FS), effect using Bezel Ship to grap Singing Lanius (SL)
  4. Activate Bezel Ship in the grave to summon it and summon SL
  5. Link summon FS and SL to make Wise Strix (WS)
  6. WS effect summon Mimicry Lanius
  7. XYZ the second FS using DS and ML
  8. FS effect, grab raider's wing by detaching ML
  9. WS effect, grab Soul Shave Force, activate it, summon Cyber dragon infinity
  10. ML in grave to grab Strangle Lanius (SL2)
  11. Raider's Wing (RW) effect to summon itself
  12. Link summon Bardiche with FS and WS
  13. Bardiche effect, dump Silent Boots, set Shade Brigantine (SB)
  14. Silent Boots effect, grab the PK RU magic, set it
  15. Summon SL2 from hand, use it's effect summon SL in the grave
  16. Activate SB and XYZ summon TT Redoer with it and Raider's Wig
  17. XYZ summon Dark rebelion using the 2 left monsters.
End board : Cyber dragon infinty, Bardiche, TT redoer with a trap, Dark Rebelion and the PK RU set and the TT trap. Opponent's turn : Activate the RU to summon Dark requiem with Dark Rebelion. ==> 5 negates and Redoer and Bardiche pop during opponent's turn.

deck_excerpt: Hora de quemar la vida de tu oponente sin que pueda usar handtraps para evitarlo. La sacerdotisa oscura llegó! Time to burn your opponent's life with
deck_description:
Deck creado por: Darklab Objetivo: Quemar la vida del oponente usando el efecto de Shadowpriestess of ohm UwU. Link a la demostración del Deck: https://youtu.be/DTn1bJ1bDmk Extenders para iniciar el combo:
  • Tour guide from the underworld: Vale x3. Trae al campo a Graff o al Edge imp (el otro lo envías al cementerio usando a Cherubini). En todo caso, es el mejor normal summon del deck.
  • Fiendish rhino warrior: Vale x2. Envía al cementerio el mismo target que la Tour guide, aunque no aprovecha el cuerpo extra. Necesita otro extender sí o sí.
  • Junk forward: Se invoca de modo especial desde la mano si no controlas monstruos, por lo que si lo robas, debe ser el primero en invocarse.
  • Kagemucha knight: Se invoca de modo especial cuando invocas otro monstruo de nivel 3 de modo normal. Ojo que puede perder timing.
  • Psychic wheelder: Se invoca si ya tienes otro monstruo de nivel 3, aunque sólo es una vez por turno.
  • Psychic tracer: Igual que el anterior.
  • Gilasaurus: Se invoca casi gratuitamente. Ojo que el rival puede invocar algo del cementerio, aunque usualmente eso no es un problema.
  • Fossil dig: Trae al Gilasaurus.
  • Foolish burial: Puedes enviar a Cloak para robar a Boots o Brigandine, o en su defecto enviar uno de los targets de la Tour guide.
  • Emergency teleport: Trae a uno de los Psychic gratis.
Inicio del combo:
  1. Primero, se debe traer a Cherubini y activar su efecto. No importa si es negado, ya que lo importante es el costo de enviar al cementerio a Graff para invocar del Deck a Cir (Ojo, si Cherubini mantiene sus efectos negados, Cir se destruirá si tenemos otros monstruos, así que cuidado).
  2. Hacemos link summon con cherubini y Cir, con lo que se activará el efecto de este último y así invocaremos nuevamente a Cherubini. El monstruo link que invocaremos dependerá de la ruta que elijamos, la cual a su vez depende de cuántos extenders tengamos disponibles.
Ruta segura (Número de extenders iniciales requerido: 4+. Monstruo: Apollousa):
  1. Al tener 2 extenders extra además de los usados para invocar a Cherubini, usaremos un material link más para ir por Apollousa. Opcionalmente si hay más extenders, se le puede invocar con 4 materiales para tener las 4 negaciones, pero siempre dejando 1 para el siguiente paso. También es importante no poner demasiados cuerpos, ya que más tarde van a estorbar.
  2. Con el extender sobrante y el Cherubini revivido por el efecto de Cir, invocaremos por link a Codebreaker virus swordsman, colinkeado a Apollousa. Esto activará el efecto de invocar del Deck a Codebreaker zero day.
  3. Ahora procederemos a invocar a Codebreaker berserker usando los dos codebreaker, siempre en el medio para invocar de vuelta los otros 2 a ambos lados usando su efecto.
  4. Usamos a los codebreaker link para invocar a Isolde. Añadimos cualquier descarte e invocamos a Armageddon knight. Para los equipos a descartar, es importante enviar Phoenix blade (combo guerrero), Sword of sparkles (ya verán) y Cursed bamboo sword (para añadirnos una magia a la mano).
  5. Armageddon enviará al cementerio a Summoner monk, y usaremos a Armageddon y Codebreaker zero day para obtener a Dugares y así invocarlo de vuelta. Es importante que ambos monstruos sean invocados donde NO apunta Apollousa.
  6. Activamos el efecto del Phoenix blade para desterrar a dos guerreros cualquiera para añadirlo a la mano y lo descartamos como el coste del Summoner monk para invocar al Rescue ferret.
  7. Nos deshacemos de Isolde con el efecto de Sword of sparkles en el cementerio y activamos el efecto de Ferret para traer a Speedroid red-eyed dice, Plaguespreader zombie y a Edge imp sabres o Phantom knights of silent boots (dependiendo si ya hemos usado uno o el otro, si no cualquier otro no tuner estará bien, pero tendremos un cuerpo menos para sacrificar más adelante)
  8. Invocamos por sincronía a Rose maiden con el Plaguespreader y el monstruo de nivel 3 que elegimos para obtener el Black garden. Traemos nuevamente el Plaguespreader con su efecto para invocar nuevamente por sincronía al Shooting riser dragon.
  9. Con el efecto del Riser dragon enviamos al cementerio el World legacy - world chalice en nuestro Deck (en realidad cualquier World legacy de nivel 6 o menor está bien) y activamos el Black garden.
  10. Invocamos a Flame swordsman usando a Summoner monk y el Speedroid dice, tras lo cual activaremos el Black garden y traeremos de vuelta al Summoner monk.
  11. Usamos el efecto de Phoenix blade para traerla a la mano por segunda vez (debería quedar por lo menos un guerrero en el cementerio todavía) y la usamos como coste del Summoner monk para traer el Pathfinder.
  12. Activamos el efecto del Pathfinder para traer a la mano el Lair of darkness (el cual activaremos) e invocamos a Lib usando al Summoner monk y el Flame swordsman.
  13. Con el efecto de Lib colocaremos el World legacy succession y nuevamente traeremos al Summoner monk.
  14. Traeremos por última vez el Phoenix blade desterrando el guerrero que quedaba y el Flame swordsman, y lo usamos de costo para el Summoner monk para traer a Shadowpriestess of ohm.
  15. Usando el efecto de Ohm nos desharemos de Lib y Dugares (1600) y usaremos al Summoner monk junto con el Riser dragon para invocar a Halqifibrax.
  16. Con Halqifibrax traemos al Speedroid den-den y usamos a ambos para invocar a Auroradon y activar su efecto, con lo que tendremos un link y 3 fichas para sacrificar con Ohm (1600 + 3200 = 4800).
  17. Para el resto, usaremos el efecto de Rose maiden para traer el Riser dragon, el efecto de Speedroid den-den para traer al Speedroid dice y el efecto de la carta de nivel 3 que elegimos (si es Sabres, se invoca solo; si es Silent boots, traemos a Brigandine y lo invocamos) (4800 + 800 + 800 + 800 = 7200)
  18. Para el último monstruo podemos usar a Apollousa o a la misma Ohm (7200 + 800 = 8000). GG. Si por alguna razón usaste a Sabres y Boots al inicio y te faltan 2 sacrificios, puedes usar ambos (Apollousa y Ohm).
Ruta parcialmente segura (Número de extenders iniciales requerido: 3. Monstruo: Tenyi)
  1. A diferencia de la primera ruta, sólo tenemos un extender adicional que debemos guardar para el codebreaker, así que usaremos solamente a Cherubini y Cir para invocar a Tenyi.
  2. El resto va igual hasta llegar al paso 7 de la ruta segura. En este punto, en lugar de activar el efecto de Sword of sparkles, usaremos a Isolde junto con Tenyi para invocar a Apollousa.
  3. El combo continúa igual hasta el final.
Tips:
  • Apollousa es útil para sacar del juego casi cualquier handtrap, aprovechando que Impermanence ya no se usa mucho y que Called está a 1 copia (por ahora 7w7)
  • Edge imp sabres y Plaguespreader zombie pueden usarse para enviar garnets en tu mano de vuelta al Deck. Algunos garnets que debes devolver serían los targets de Rescue Ferret o Armageddon Knight y el monstruo World legacy.
  • Si tienes el Sword of sparkles o el Phoenix blade en la mano, puedes descartarlo en el primer uso del Summoner monk.
  • Si tienes al Armageddon knight en tu mano, puedes invocar en su lugar al Dark grepher, usando como coste al Armageddon knight.
  • Link spider ayuda a Brigandine a ser usado para invocar al Codebreaker swordsman.
  • Si robas el Black garden, puedes usarlo como coste del Summoner monk, ya que el efecto de Rose maiden lo añadirá del cementerio a tu mano más adelante.
  • No encontré cómo hacer el combo con 2 extenders, ya que es necesario ir por los codebreaker y no tenemos a Halqifibrax disponible porque lo usaremos luego (si encuentran una forma quiero saberla 7w7).
Pros:
  • Deck extremadamente consistente, tiene pocos bricks y/o garnets.
  • Versátil. Se adapta a los recursos que tengamos en mano.
  • Protegido constantemente por Apollousa, por lo que es difícil de contrarrestarlo una vez toca el campo.
  • No requiere tanta exactitud, varias invocaciones pueden hacerse con otros materiales link, por ejemplo, y de cometerse pequeños errores es posible volver al camino.
  • No requiere demasiados recursos para realizar el combo, con 3 es suficiente para iniciar.
  • Puede baitear hantraps tempranas con los extenders suficientes.
Contras:
  • El Deck depende del burn finito, por lo que si el oponente activa cartas como Ghost sister u otras que aumenten sus LP, será gg.
  • Aún teniendo protección, el Deck es susceptible a Nibiru, Impermanence y Called by the grave si son usados correctamente.
  • A pesar de ser consistente, se requieren 3+ Extenders para funcionar, lo cual puede no pasar a veces.
  • Si destruyen a Cherubini antes de activar su efecto y no hay forma de invocarlo del cementerio, también es gg.

deck_excerpt: A cool, budget-friendly deck incorporating some of the strongest decks in the current meta!
deck_description: An affordable and powerful deck that can handle any situation! 60 cards allows you to fit all the powerful options you need. The only downside is that it's kind of difficult to shuffle such a big deck lol. Running the Dragoon package of course, because it's a powerful boss monster. Same with Ulimate Conductor Tyranno. With Double Evolution Pill you just need one Dino in your hand or GY, and Misc/Archosaur can help you get there consistently. Eldlich is overall a strong archetype, and all the spell cards makes it easy to summon Golden Lord. Ten Thousand Dragon is great for OTK'ing your opponent in one attack. Catches your opponent off-guard, and is very satisfying to pull off! Dogmatika is good at disrupting your opponent. Invoked lets you get to Mechaba for more negates, and there are plenty of light-attribute targets in the deck. Dragonmaids are an interesting tech option I've been exploring to unbrick if you aren't able to summon 10k Dragon. Similarly, the Evil HEROs are quite powerful and difficult to deal with. Aside from the main archetypes, some solid competitive staples are included because you can't really go wrong with them.  The extra deck is mostly straightforward, with the fusion monsters being associated with the above archetypes. Gustav Max is easy to go into with Golden Lord, UCT, and 10k Dragon all being level 10. From there you can burn and go into Liebe for massive damage, and if they're still alive somehow you go into Zeus! Underworld Goddess is a great removal option since linking your opponent's monsters gets around pretty much all forms of protection. Accesscode, BLS, and Anaconda are insane. Anima is good to go into from Archosaur, and stealing your opponent's monster is pretty cool.  Overall, I think this is a very powerful deck that pretty much anyone can afford. It is a highly unpredictable deck that can switch from slow control style to fast-paced OTK. It has outs for any situation I could think of. The only thing is I wanted to incorporate Drytrons as well, but the special summon restriction makes it hard to work. Regardless, I could see this becoming a Tier 1 or maybe even Tier 0 deck in the near future!  If this deck is still a little outside your price range, feel free to swap Infinite Impermanence for Effect Veiler.

The dragonmaid archetype is one based off of (loosely) the anime Kobayashi's Dragon Maid, where the humanoid "maid" dragons have bigger dragon forms. In practice, the deck is basically boneless dragon link with a slightly more control oriented and grind-game focused gameplan. Featuring an omni-negate boss monster (Sheou), and various starters to gain access to your fusion spell and 30 million extenders, this deck is probably the main deck to make use of the Hieratic link monster. The deck can make use of dragon link-esque guardragon combos, as well as various interruptions in the form of the hieratic link, and the trap Dragonmaid Tidying.  tl;dr dragon maid waifus gain advantage every turn because of their angry boss monster who turns into her normal self after saying no as well as going +2 every standby phase.  Pls R/F with suggestions to main/extra. Side deck subject to change based on local metagame IRL but it's one I just made for online play.

deck_excerpt: A going-first combo variant of Appliancers
deck_description: The goal of this deck is to go first and make a Dragoon under Gryphon lock with at least one Fog Blade set; a board I have dubbed "The Cross". The deck needs its entire hand to function, so if your board gets broken you're SOL When handtrapped you might still have some wiggle room to squeeze out a Dragoon or I:P + Dragoon for some basic interruption.  This deck can't go second. Win the die roll.  The side deck is format dependent, but the Gameciels and Dark Rulers have stuck around for a while in an attempt to mitigate the going second problem. If you really wanna make going second not suck, you can side in the cards to swap your Dragoon engine for a Rainbow Neos engine in game 2.

deck_description: I made this deck after looking at some other decks and found them a bit too big-brain synchro spammy for my small xyz player mind to handle so I made this. It relies almost entirely on summoning speeder and throwing trail in the graveyard. I added both regular majestic and shooting star because they both list Stardust Dragon in their card text to give Shooting Majestic an extra attack.  Easy Beginner deck for synchro players who're just starting out and learning how to use the mechanic and helps about learning activation timing with how Arriving Miracle and Stardust Trail interact.

I found playing Onomat ZW's to be really fun so I made this deck and decided to share it. There's a WHOLE bunch of searching going on so it's pretty weak to disruption. but if it all works out well enough you can get two really strong monsters on board.     Really easy to learn deck and if you play your cards right you can get a 10,000+ attack Dragonic Utopia Ray with several equips and a Utopic Future Dragon on board.

deck_excerpt: Fossil Adam with guide because this is the deck I use the most
deck_description:
My primary online deck, rocks all the way

List:

Main deck:

3 weathering soldier (search for anything fossil related)

3 koki muru guardian (common step taken against Nibiru)

3 adamacipator analyzer (quick starter and extender in cases)

2 rock band xenogataur (recycle, underrated, it’s like it was made for adams)

3 predaplant orphys scorpio (darlantian cobra, discard a rock and make wonders)

1 predaplant darlaintian cobra (search fossil fusion)

3 flint cragger (mill a fossil, used on skullgar)

3 adamacipator researcher (extender, great card)

3 adamacipator seeker (extender, another great card)

3 doki doki (because adamacipator broke it)

3 adamacipator signs (extender for otks)

3 fossil fusion (star of the show, fossil fusion is great card)

3 miracle rupture (search fossil fusion, or upstart and foolish, great card)

2 time stream (the main way to get skullgios)

1 foolish burial (because that’s what’s up)

1 upstart goblin (here’s 1000 life points, I’ll kill you turn 1 anyways)

Extra

1 fossil dragon skullgios (double attack plus double piecing damage times 3500 attack stat = otks like crazy)

1 fossil warrior skull knight (removal, only used for that)

2 fossil dragon skullgar (fossil fusion search for flint cragger)

1 fossil warrior skull bone (time stream extender)

1 crystal wing synchro dragon (negate, just in case, mostly used though for the attack boost)

1 adamacipator risen dragite (removal that wins me games a lot of the time)

1 adamacipator risen leonite (extender)

2 adamacipator risen raptite (extender)

1 herald of the arc light (like crystal wing, negate just in case)

1 gallant granite (searcher for extension)

1 leviair, the sea dragon (combo piece in the scorpio combo)

1 crystron halquibrax (because why not)

1 borrelsword dragon (another consistent boss that comes out often, mostly to clear up space though but double attack plus attack steal helps otks)

As you may have noticed I mentioned a orphys scorpio combo frequently,

Going second, opponent has monster in grave with level 4 or less, orphys scorpio is in hand with weathering soldier, darlainian cobra is in deck (looks conditional but it’s not really though)

Normal scorpio

Pitch soldier to summon cobra

Cobra search fossil fusion, soldier search time stream

Activate fusion, fuse soldier with monster from opponent’s grave to make fossil warrior skull bone

Time stream skull bone for skull knight

Skull bone effect banish to add other time stream

Time stream skull knight to summon skullgios

Overlay scorpio and cobra to summon leviair the sea dragon

Skull knight effect, banish destroy opponents monster

Leviair effect detach summon skull knight.

Two fossils (including skullgios) and leviair for the end board,

You mostly use scorpio to get fossil fusion and leviair though.

Adamacipator is random so the fossil side in this deck are the only with actual fixed and no variables in their combos.

Wing it and be going blind second.

deck_excerpt: Competitive built Dream Mirrors with a heavy Chaos engine, can go first or second building around 2-4 interruptions.
deck_description:
Made to go first but can side to go second. You want to get Mara on board with joy to grab Oneiromancy or Black Knight, if you cant then you go fully into chaos combo's. Dangers are their to help get extra monsters on board and to add extra Allure of Darkness targets, I suggest only using them once you use all your important cards unless you have Effect Veiler in hand. If you are able to keep you normal summon by getting one for one, you can extend with Effect Veiler to make Halqifibrax which can then climb into Selene or Unicorn, depending on if you have enough spells in grave and on field. More optional cards are:
  • Chaos Daedelus unless you want to add Hypnagogia.
  • Dream Mirror Disciple as its just an extender for Phantasms if you are unable to get the correct field spell with Mara although it does make using Set Rotation alot safer as you can return the field spell back to hand.
  • Effect Veiler, Halqifibrax and Selene if the cost is too high or you would rather run some other extra deck options and alternative hand traps (preferably light/dark).
