deck_excerpt: Chaos Hieratics prototype for combo-labbing Darkflare recursion accessed by 1-card Spheres engines, tributed by a Hieratic
deck_description:
[Combo-labbing prototype: Darkflare Recursion] This version of the Chaos Hieratics prototype deck now heavily leans into 1-card Spheres engines (namely the Dragonmaids). After REDMD was errata'd, I aimed to loop Darkflare instead. Luckily, there has been wave-after-wave of Dragon support lately, and plenty of cards (such as Armed Dragon Thunder LV5) benefit the Dragon decks in general and the Darkflare loop. Built with 2 key challenges in-mind: * Can play thru Nibiru after 5th summon * Recur Darkflare for advantage Current full-combo field: GY has: 1) Brotaur 2) Tempest 3) Dragunity Arma Gram 4) Galactic Spiral Dragon Combo packets:
  • Combo packet 1 builds advantage and can be toolboxed for different match-ups (link here). Milling Armed Dragon LV5 instead of Galactic Spiral accesses combo packet 2.
  • Combo packet 2 uses Tempest + Arma Gram to search a small chaos dragon/Dragonmaid (if normal summon is unused)/Hieratic. Then, it goes into Apollousa and builds advantage to use combo packet 1.
  • Combo packet 3 is a Halqi-Auroradon combo. If Nibiru goes off before making Apollousa, the field will have a Hieratic to summon a tuner. This is a Dragon, so if your hand has an extender, you can choose between Romulus or Halqi

Chaos Hieratics (02-21-21)

Monsters 1x Flamvell Guard 1x Eset 3x Su 3x Nebthet 1x Black Dragon Collapserpent 1x White Dragon Wyverburster 1x Black Metal Dragon 1x Red-Eyes Darkness Metal Dragon 2x Noctovision Dragon 2-3x Parlor Dragonmaid 2-3x Chamber Dragonmaid (1x Nurse Dragonmaid)

Combo packet 1: Rank 8s 1x Omni Dragon Brotaur 1x Darkflare Dragon 1x Galactic Spiral Dragon Combo packet 2: WIND Dragon plus-ing engine 1x Armed Dragon Thunder LV5 1x Tempest, Dragon Ruler of Storms 1x Dragunity Arma Gram (1x Dragunity Guisarme) Combo packet 3: Playing thru Nibiru 1x Deskbot 001 1x Mecha Phantom Beast Coltwing

Spells/Traps 3x Hieratic Seal of Convocation 2x Monster Gate 3x Chaos Space 1x Dragonmaid Hospitality 1x Dragonmaid Tidying 1x Dragunity Glow (1x Dragunity Divine Lance) (1x Boot Sector Launch) (1x Monster Reborn)

Extra Deck Combo packet 1: Rank 8s 1x Striker Dragon 1x Hieratic Seal of The Heavenly Spheres 2x Number 38: Hope Harbinger Dragon Titanic Galaxy (1x Number 97: Draglubion) (1x Number 99: Utopic Dragon) Combo packet 2: Apollousa & Galaxy Satellite 1x Dragunity Knight – Romulus 1x Apollousa, Bow the of Goddess 1x Guardragon Elpy 1x Guardragon Pisty 1x Galaxy Satellite Dragon Combo packet 3: Halqi off Nibiru 1x Crystron Halqifibrax 1x Mecha Phantom Beast Auroradon 2x Herald of the Arc Light

------- ------- Optional cards in parentheses ------- This field with Darkflare and REDMD (both effects unused) can access just about any dragon. Some examples:
  • VFD {World Legacy Guardragon Mardark + Trishula, the Dragon of Icy Imprisonment}
  • Light and Darkness Dragon
    • (send "Samsara Dragon" (pre-release), link away Darkflare to rez with REDMD, dump LaDD, Samsara eff)
  • Horus LV8 (send & rez Horus LV8, needs Level Up! in-hand)
  • 2 Rank 8 XYZs
  • 1 Rank 8 and 1 Rank 4 XYZs
  • Five-Headed Link Dragon
  • Dragonmaid Sheou (send and rez a DMaid to access Dragomaid Changeover)
  • Tzolkin (send Galactic Spiral and rez a tuner (like a Dragunity tuner from Divine Lance))
  • Infinite Bird Negate (Simorgh, Mist Valley Apex Avian, Mist Valley Thunder Bird equipped by Union Carrier)
    • Link-2 {Pisty + Darkflare} after send & rez a LV4 (like Chamber Dragonmaid), make Force Strix {Chamber Dmaid +  WyverColla} to get Singing Lanius, make Union Carrier & Simorgh
    • If WyverColla was used for Apollousa, Arma Gram + WIND Dragon (like Parlor Dmaid) sent & rez can make Harpie Conductor, make Union Carrier & Simorgh
  • Borrelend + Borreload Savage + Link-4 (with Rokket engine)
  • Cyberse Clock Dragon/Millennium-eyes Restrict/etc.
    • Link-2 {Pisty + Darkflare} after send & rez a LV2 tuner + WyverColla to synchro Muddy Mudragon (can make "Albion the Stigmata Dragon" (pre-release) as an intermediate monster)
  • Saryuja and Chaos Ruler, the Chaotic Magical Dragon into VFD {fusion Trish + Crocodragon} for draw 3 (Rose Dragons preferred)
  • etc. (Armed Dragons, Blue-Eyes, Red-Eyes...)
My latest boards have focused on turn 3 with floaters in the GY like Arma Gram, Chaos Ruler, Tempest, Brotaur, and Galactic Spiral... maybe Phantom Knights backrow. As noted, this is a very casual deck I experiment with to play with friends Other ideas: * Haven’t added 1.5-card Spheres engines (to dilute the combo pieces) since these combo pieces so far aren’t horrible in-hand… and Dragunity Remus w/ Guisarme could be a nice discard engine * Hieratic Seal of Creation: Personally reallllly like to send it to the GY (Foolish Burial Goods/Brotaur) because it can revive Spheres...& Hieratic+Brotaur+Spheres is a fast Apollusa * Rose Dragons are really powerful fun (& Roxrose is a 1-card Spheres!), but for consistency, I’d likely add a copy of each Dragonmaid instead...? * Armed Dragon LV7, LV3, & Flash with Twin Triangle are powerful but VERY clunky (fun tho) * Pile Armed Dragon is good but doesn’t seem to have enough unique advantages over Darkflare in this build (currently. Will keep in mind) * Avoided Rokkets for a deckbuilding challenge, may optimized with it again soon * Removed Seyfert since this deck has plenty of normal summons & already likes to search the small chaos dragons with Tempest, may consider 1 copy * Abhyss: could replace Halqi-Auroradon as a Nibiru back-up plan if drawn into * Stardust Synchron: could replace Halqi-Auroradon as a Nibiru back-up plan if drawn into, currently looking for ways to make & destroy Chaofeng to search it (not necessary, just for curiosity) * Been thinking about adding Dogmatika+Shadolls * If anyone wants to shrink this deck size, I’d recommend removing some of my combo pieces to build your deck with a Codebreakers and Phantom Knights engine Hieratic Discord link: discord.com/invite/rmdXrbX EXTRA DECK combo order: right-to-left for playtesting in EDOPro

deck_excerpt: Basic Sky Striker Deck with no mine or floodgates, and increased consistency for less feels bad moment. Uses Halq, Selene, Acesscode to end games. Doe
deck_description: This is not a particularly optimized deck list for competitiveness, but it avoids alot of my feels bad moment like drawing 2 copies of the handtrap or some garnet and it doesnt play floodgates.   3x Raye: It starts your engine and keeps it going. 3x Roze: Its extra copies of Raye that can occasionally help steal games. Can be bricky, but I prefer opening it with Raye then not having link access at all. It also helps in outing Dragoon by running over Verte and negating Dragoon, and then using Zeke/Afterburner to delay/remove threat. 3x Area Zero: Helps even out your hands, and a goodextender to close games. 3x Shark Cannon: Its graveyard disruption helps alot, and revive can leads to interesting game states. 3x Window Anchor: Disruption, and help close out games by attacking with the monster you steal. 2x Afterburner: Removal for chunky monsters. Feel free to use it as a way to pop Area Zero or using it on your own monster to get rid of a backrow. 1x Jamming Wave: Remove unknown backrow, but the non targeting destruction is also good. 1x Drone: Consistency Booster, might be used as a extender to link climb, but it haven't came up for me. 1x Eagle Booster: A really funny one-of, I use it to protect Shizuku in the end phase or Accesscode against Nibiru(Selene summoning veiler is the 5th summon tho) and during your opponents turn. 1xMultirole : Help clean up your MMZ, clear the way for your spells, and get tons of advantage. 2x Foolish Burial Goods: 3 is a bit too much since its HOPT, and it allows you to use Kagari without using Hayate. It also helps with the spell count in grave. 1x Metalfoes Fusion: There are a lot of ways to pop this, so drawing it doesn't hurt too bad, and it makes Foolish Burial Goods another way to draw Raye, and Area Zero into a +1 2x Pot of Desires: It's a really good card, but since the decks has 4 cycle cards, I feel comfortable with how much I see it. Also, its HOPT, and I dont like banishing 20 cards. 2x Forbidden Droplets: Dragoon out, and can fulfil the 3x spells in grave cost by sending the activated spells on the field as cost. The half attack is really neat. I play 2 because widow anchor does the same thing most of the time. 2x Ash Blossom: Disruption 2x Ghost Ogre: Disruption 2x Belle: Disruption 2x Veiler: Disruption, but also needed for the halq selene combo 1x Reinforcement of the Army: Find Raye or Roze Terraforming: Extra Spells in the grave Ice Dragon Prison: Dragoon out #3 Upstart: Free Spell   Turn 1: Objective: Not Die Try to get a Sky Striker link on board, and set up your disruption. Foolish Burial Goods to get a Anchor or a Shark Cannon, or Multirole if you can benefit from the resetting during the EP. *If you have multirole, you can search Anchor during EP with Shizuku and use it on her to reset using multirole. Turn 2-3: Objective: Establish Parity and 3+ Spells in Grave If you went first, try to disrupt your opponent so that that you will have Raye during the EP. If you went second, try to break the board while making sure Raye stays in rotation. If you manage to establish 3+ spells in grave, use the additionally effects of Window Anchor to go into Zeke to remove 2 monsters. Make sure to chip in extra damage, since Accesscode can't kill them from 8000.   Turn 3-4: Objective: Establish a winning position If its your turn, use the empowered effect of your spells to accelerate in card advantage or look for ways to get end the game. Look for stray tuners, and some combination of Window Anchor, Raye and Roze with Area Zero. If its your opponent's turn, evaluate your cards in hand and consider saving cards like Widow Anchor and Shark Cannon to end the game. Acesscode talker can usually clear 4 cards easily, so letting them build a field might not be the worst idea if your Window Anchor and Shark Cannon can be used more aggressively.   Turn 5+: Objective: Win At this point, multirole should likely be in play, and with 3+ spells in grave, each of your spells generate +2-3 card advantage. However, Sky Striker links are likely almost depleted, so make sure at all point to look for ways to kill your opponent. At I find 6 thousand life is my standard reach in most games. I can clear the board, Summon Raye and Roze, and pop Area Zero to get the 3rd copy, and deal 6k with Raye summoning the last striker link during combat.   Cards to not run: Scissor Cross: Its a neat card to play since it helps you end games way easier, but your most important objective is to survive turn 1-2 and let your cards out advantage your opponent. You can maybe consider cutting Roze for this Shizuku search as insurance, but it feels bricky and win more.   Hercules Base: This gives the deck a great amount of grind, Kagari can recur this ad infinitum, but it doesn't help me survive when I need to, and I should be winning when Hercules Base is getting value.   Utopia Double: I don't like Double or Nothing, loses to ash and desires.   Pot of Avarice: It bricks turn 1, and it bricks when you don't have Raye. This is when you are most vulnerable, so I don't run it. It feels great when it resolves though.   Toon Table of Content: Might be okay when it was MR4 with Toon Cyber Dragon and Engage, but getting 3 spells early isn't worth it for it.   Dragoon: Its not fun for me or other people, and its bricky.   Cards to Consider: Cosmic Cyclone: Its difficult to get rid of face up spell and traps without waiting a few turns.   Handtraps: They are mostly flex spots except for veiler, so feel free to swap those anytime.   Borrelsword/Generic Link: Sometime I find myself with awkward amount of materials to link climb with.   Relinquished Anima : Turns a level one into a spellcaster for Selene. It can be useful if you find yourself with crow in your hand or opponent's graveyard.   Called by the Grave: Its good, but people really like playing Gamma.   Triple Tactical Talent: Maybe for going second, but I am not sure how I feel about this.

Try to use armed dragon as engine to summon big synchros:  Start with the windwitches, best case with windwitch icebell -> do standard windwitch combos, but safe the lvl 1 tuner for the Armed dragon part. Normal summon a armed dragon, then tag out into the lv 5 and go for a 6 synchro, or go for the lv 7 dragon and make a lvl 8 synchro.

deck_excerpt: Scrap Raptor deck w/ a Kaiju engine
deck_description: ...I gotta get on my grind. Anyways, this is a Scrap Kaiju deck featuring Scrap Raptor, one of the best cards that Scraps have gotten in a long time. When I read Scrap Raptor's effects, I figured out that it plus Interrupted Kaiju Slumber or Scrap Factory can lead to an OTK. By himself, Scrap Raptor is a 1-card Avramax that was Link Summoned with I:P Masquerena!       Anyways, this deck's whole goal is to go second and OTK. Because of Scrap Raptor's effects, you wanna draw this card or a card that searches it as often as possible. But if you have to go first, use Scrap Raptor's effects to summon Mekk-Knight Crusadia Avramax with I:P Masquerena.     As for this deck's name,  I named it after "Godzilla Interception Operation Awaji", a real-life tourist attraction on Awaji Island, Japan. Godzilla Interception Operation Awaji is part of the Nijigen No Mori theme park on said island. It comes with 4 main parts:   1. A theatre playing a short exclusive film. To keep with the theme of GIOA, those who come to it will be sent to the theater, where they will watch a 7-minute short film explaining why Godzilla is on Awaji Island. It also explains what the other parts are.   2. A Godzilla zipline and statue. Inside GIOA, there is a 65-foot/20-meter tall, 180-foot/55-meter long statue of Shin Godzilla with his mouth open. There are two ziplines which allow guests to actually glide in Shin Godzilla's mouth!   3. A shooting game. There's also a game in which people can pick up fake guns and shoot at Godzilla's cells.   4. The official Godzilla Museum. Godzilla Interception Operation Awaji has the world's first-ever permanent Godzilla-themed museum. The Godzilla Museum features dioramas of scenes from the films, as well as figures of the monsters, and material involving the Godzilla movies in general!  So if any of you plan on going to Japan once the COVID-19 pandemic is over, BOOM! Now you have a good reason to!
